WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:09.274
<i> ["This Will Be (An Everlasting</i>
<i> Love)"]</i>
<i> ♪♪♪</i>

00:09.310 --> 00:14.113
♪

00:14.148 --> 00:17.950
♪<i> Ooh ooh Ooh ooh</i> ♪

00:17.985 --> 00:22.121
♪<i> Ooh ooh oh yeah</i> ♪

00:22.156 --> 00:25.524
♪<i> Mm mm mm mm</i> ♪

00:25.559 --> 00:33.699
♪

00:33.734 --> 00:35.501
♪<i> This will be</i> ♪

00:35.536 --> 00:37.302
♪<i> An everlasting love</i> ♪

00:37.338 --> 00:39.271
♪<i> This will be</i> ♪

00:39.306 --> 00:41.173
♪<i> The one I've waited for</i> ♪

00:41.208 --> 00:42.841
♪<i> This will be</i> ♪

00:42.877 --> 00:46.979
♪<i> The first time anyone</i>
<i> has loved me,</i> ♪

00:47.014 --> 00:48.881
♪<i> oh oh oh</i> ♪

00:48.916 --> 00:50.816
♪<i> I'm so glad</i> ♪

00:50.851 --> 00:52.618
♪<i> He found me in time</i> ♪

00:52.653 --> 00:54.987
♪<i> And I'm so glad that</i> ♪

00:55.022 --> 00:56.155
[sighs]

00:56.190 --> 00:57.723
Have fun, dress.

00:57.758 --> 01:00.559
This is your only day outside.

01:00.594 --> 01:03.996
[sighs]

01:04.031 --> 01:06.632
♪<i> Loving you</i> ♪

01:06.667 --> 01:16.642
[cheering and applause]

01:16.677 --> 01:20.212
♪

01:20.247 --> 01:23.015
♪<i> This will be an</i>
<i> everlasting love.</i> ♪

01:23.050 --> 01:24.483
As many of you know,

01:24.518 --> 01:27.152
I have been
in a lot of weddings.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.153
[crowd laughs]

01:28.189 --> 01:30.422
Nine, to be exact,
and I think on the tenth,

01:30.458 --> 01:31.857
I get a set of steak knives.

01:31.892 --> 01:33.258
[crowd laughs]

01:33.294 --> 01:34.893
But in all seriousness,

01:34.929 --> 01:37.029
I have had the great pleasure
of witnessing

01:37.064 --> 01:39.431
true love in all of its glory.

01:39.467 --> 01:40.699
[crowd awes]

01:40.734 --> 01:43.602
First with my own parents, who
fell in love the day they met.

01:43.637 --> 01:45.070
[crowd awes]

01:45.106 --> 01:48.507
But also, the reason
we're here today.

01:48.542 --> 01:50.075
Allie and Dan.

01:50.111 --> 01:52.611
<i> [guests cheering]</i>

01:52.646 --> 01:56.348
You may ask, how do I know these
two are so meant to be?

01:56.383 --> 01:58.884
And no, it's not on account
of all my experience

01:58.919 --> 02:00.586
standing up here.

02:00.621 --> 02:01.854
[crowd laughs]

02:01.889 --> 02:04.456
I know, because when you
find the one,

02:04.492 --> 02:06.258
when you find your person,

02:06.293 --> 02:08.961
everything in life
falls into place.

02:08.996 --> 02:09.862
<i> Aww...</i>

02:09.897 --> 02:11.063
It's effortless.

02:11.098 --> 02:13.966
And I see that in you two
every day.

02:14.001 --> 02:17.803
So let's raise our glass
to Allie and Dan.

02:17.838 --> 02:20.973
May love always
remain effortless.

02:21.008 --> 02:28.247
[cheering and applause]

02:32.820 --> 02:35.454
Thank you for making
my something new.

02:35.489 --> 02:36.922
I love it.

02:36.957 --> 02:38.423
And I can't tell you
how many compliments

02:38.459 --> 02:39.925
I've gotten on this necklace.

02:39.960 --> 02:41.426
It could be your career,
you know?

02:41.462 --> 02:43.595
I already have a career:
insurance.

02:43.631 --> 02:45.164
And the business is going
to be all mine

02:45.199 --> 02:46.632
in about four months.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.467
Becks.

02:48.502 --> 02:50.169
This is your passion.

02:50.204 --> 02:52.804
Look, my parents are giving me
an incredible gift,

02:52.840 --> 02:54.606
a company they built
from nothing,

02:54.642 --> 02:57.643
and I consider myself very lucky
that they're entrusting me

02:57.678 --> 02:59.144
with it so they can retire.

02:59.180 --> 03:00.312
Now, come on.

03:00.347 --> 03:02.848
We are not spending your
entire wedding in the bathroom,

03:02.883 --> 03:06.285
there is a conga line out there
with your name on it.

03:06.320 --> 03:08.687
And some cute single guys
from Dan's work.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.923
[chuckles]

03:10.958 --> 03:12.758
Do you know how many people meet
their match at weddings?

03:12.793 --> 03:13.559
How many?

03:13.594 --> 03:15.360
Well, I don't have
an exact number.

03:15.396 --> 03:16.428
[laughs]

03:16.463 --> 03:17.629
But it's definitely a lot.

03:17.665 --> 03:18.997
And I am happy for all of them,

03:19.033 --> 03:21.967
but Dylan and I just broke up
a month ago.

03:22.002 --> 03:25.204
Look, he was a good guy, but it
wasn't right between you two.

03:25.239 --> 03:27.339
And I tried so hard
to make it right,

03:27.374 --> 03:28.574
but I can't do that anymore.

03:28.609 --> 03:33.345
I am okay with waiting until
I'm sure I've found my match.

03:34.415 --> 03:38.550
One more down, just the two
of us single gals left.

03:38.586 --> 03:40.719
Oh, please Lucie.

03:40.754 --> 03:42.654
You will be engaged
by Friday.

03:42.690 --> 03:43.655
Saturday.

03:43.691 --> 03:44.723
Date night.

03:44.758 --> 03:45.290
[laughs]

03:45.326 --> 03:46.391
So you better get ready.

03:46.427 --> 03:48.727
Just give me a minute to recover
from this one first.

03:48.762 --> 03:51.463
It's only because no one is a
better Maid of Honour than you.

03:51.498 --> 03:53.332
There wasn't a dry eye
in the house.

03:53.367 --> 03:59.004
Now, all you single ladies
get on the dance floor.

03:59.039 --> 04:03.675
It's time to toss the bouquet.

04:03.711 --> 04:08.213
(crowd): One, two, three!

04:08.249 --> 04:13.151
[cheering and applause]

04:23.197 --> 04:24.529
Congratulations!

04:24.565 --> 04:33.005
[dance music]
♪

04:33.040 --> 04:34.106
Do you mind if we sit here?

04:34.141 --> 04:35.741
My feet are on fire.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.042
Of course.

04:37.077 --> 04:38.277
You guys worked hard out there,

04:38.312 --> 04:40.112
plus it's almost barefoot
time anyway.

04:40.147 --> 04:42.180
Oh, you do know
the wedding game?

04:42.216 --> 04:44.349
We'll leave just as soon as
your date gets back.

04:44.385 --> 04:45.751
Oh, no date.

04:45.786 --> 04:47.252
So, take a load off.

04:47.288 --> 04:48.387
No date?

04:48.422 --> 04:49.955
A beauty like you?

04:49.990 --> 04:51.957
Well, it's a lot
of responsibility,

04:51.992 --> 04:53.358
being the Maid of Honour.

04:53.394 --> 04:55.560
I don't need to entertain
a date all night.

04:55.596 --> 04:58.030
Well, my nephew
Spencer's available.

04:58.065 --> 05:00.232
He's about your age,
and he just left his wife.

05:00.267 --> 05:02.234
No. You need to meet my son,
Devin.

05:02.269 --> 05:04.903
He's single and ready
to mingle.

05:04.938 --> 05:06.805
They both sound so great,

05:06.840 --> 05:10.275
but we don't have to go
looking for it.

05:10.311 --> 05:14.880
When it's right, love just hits
you like a ton of bricks, right?

05:14.915 --> 05:16.248
[slow soul music]
♪♪

05:16.283 --> 05:18.383
Oh, Gladys.
It's my song.

05:18.419 --> 05:20.152
I'm going back in,
sore feet or not.

05:20.187 --> 05:21.253
[laughs]

05:21.288 --> 05:22.988
Well, in case you change
your mind,

05:23.023 --> 05:25.457
here's Devin's card.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.392
When I meet an unmarried beauty
like you,

05:27.428 --> 05:29.461
I just can't help myself.

05:29.496 --> 05:31.263
Call him?

05:31.298 --> 05:34.633
I will certainly consider it.

05:34.668 --> 05:37.736
[chuckles]

05:37.771 --> 05:39.404
[sighs]

05:39.440 --> 05:44.843
♪<i> Time, yeah I'm up</i>
<i> on this...</i> ♪

05:44.878 --> 05:49.614
That is what I was waiting for,
thank you.

05:49.650 --> 05:52.417
Anything else you'd like to say
to Allie and Dan?

05:52.453 --> 05:54.619
Didn't your mother teach you
you never interrupt a lady

05:54.655 --> 05:56.955
when she's shovelling cake
in her mouth?

05:56.990 --> 05:58.357
I was trying to beat you
to the bite,

05:58.392 --> 05:59.524
but you're quick.

05:59.560 --> 06:00.659
[laughs]

06:00.694 --> 06:01.827
Apparently, I have
terrible timing.

06:01.862 --> 06:03.362
I'm just trying to take
a little break

06:03.397 --> 06:07.032
before the bride
beckons me again.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.467
Is this piece spoken for?

06:08.502 --> 06:11.169
Nope, just sitting there,
lonely, dejected,

06:11.205 --> 06:13.472
here at the single's table
waiting for a home.

06:13.507 --> 06:15.440
Then I feel a distinct
obligation to give it one.

06:15.476 --> 06:17.042
You want to be careful,
though.

06:17.077 --> 06:19.177
If you stay here too long,
those two will have you married

06:19.213 --> 06:23.348
to some obscure family member
by Friday.

06:23.384 --> 06:25.951
You know, I can't Friday.
Poker night.

06:25.986 --> 06:26.852
My loss.

06:26.887 --> 06:28.387
[chuckles]

06:28.422 --> 06:29.855
Kyle Taylor.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.890
Documentarian by day,
videographer by night.

06:31.925 --> 06:32.958
Becca Foster.

06:32.993 --> 06:37.529
Insurance sales by day,
bridal assistant by night.

06:37.564 --> 06:38.764
So...

06:38.799 --> 06:40.866
Where do you think Allie and
Dan will be 10 years from now?

06:40.901 --> 06:42.167
You just did it again.

06:42.202 --> 06:43.902
You have terrible timing.

06:43.937 --> 06:45.871
That's it, I quit.
I'm out.

06:45.906 --> 06:47.506
Well, at least you got
the ceremony.

06:47.541 --> 06:50.075
Yeah. And your speech.

06:50.110 --> 06:51.510
You really believe all that?

06:51.545 --> 06:54.746
Love is effortless, etc, etc?

06:54.782 --> 06:55.814
What, you don't?

06:55.849 --> 06:58.850
You're surrounded by love
and weddings every day.

06:58.886 --> 07:00.986
Yeah, and I see a lot
of messy stuff.

07:01.021 --> 07:02.554
I just edit it out
of the final video.

07:02.589 --> 07:06.324
Nothing is effortless,
least of all love.

07:06.360 --> 07:11.229
♪

07:11.265 --> 07:12.664
Back to work.

07:12.699 --> 07:13.865
Good luck.

07:13.901 --> 07:14.833
Actually, I meant you.

07:14.868 --> 07:17.002
<i> Ooh.</i>

07:17.037 --> 07:18.603
It's okay, we'll get it out.

07:18.639 --> 07:19.905
Don't... Blot it, blot it.

07:19.940 --> 07:22.107
<i> Quick...</i>

07:22.142 --> 07:23.775
<i> I need water, water...</i>

07:23.811 --> 07:26.845
Excuse me, we're gonna need
some club soda asap,

07:26.880 --> 07:29.881
and do not clear that plate.

07:37.458 --> 07:39.024
Thank you so much.

07:39.059 --> 07:39.858
Oh, these look--

07:39.893 --> 07:41.460
I am so sorry I'm late.

07:41.495 --> 07:43.228
All this last minute shopping
and packing,

07:43.263 --> 07:44.496
I am completely overwhelmed.

07:44.531 --> 07:47.265
Okay, I will go to Hawaii with
you if it makes you feel better.

07:47.301 --> 07:49.401
I got you a latte.

07:49.436 --> 07:50.268
Oh, thank you.

07:50.304 --> 07:52.070
Thank you.

07:53.140 --> 07:58.376
I have the instructions,
and the keys.

07:58.412 --> 08:00.245
I've watched Arlo before.

08:00.280 --> 08:03.582
Yes, but he's on
a special diet now.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.217
I feel like he's super
self-conscious

08:05.252 --> 08:07.152
so try not to shame him.

08:07.187 --> 08:08.453
Don't worry about anything.

08:08.489 --> 08:10.555
You just go, have fun
on your honeymoon.

08:10.591 --> 08:12.991
But this may be the last time
I can cat-sit,

08:13.026 --> 08:14.459
because once I take
over the business,

08:14.495 --> 08:15.827
that's going to be 24/7.

08:15.863 --> 08:16.695
I know.

08:16.730 --> 08:18.997
Are you sure this
is what you want?

08:19.032 --> 08:22.234
Of course, yes, this has always
been the plan.

08:22.269 --> 08:24.302
You don't seem super excited
about it.

08:24.338 --> 08:27.739
What, no, I'm excited,
this is just a lot of pressure.

08:27.774 --> 08:30.442
You know, my parents built this
business from the ground up,

08:30.477 --> 08:33.278
so I can't let it go down
on my watch.

08:33.313 --> 08:34.479
And there's no one better.

08:34.515 --> 08:37.415
That's why they feel comfortable
leaving it in your hands.

08:37.451 --> 08:39.150
Thank you.

08:39.186 --> 08:41.419
...Wait, isn't that?...

08:41.455 --> 08:43.688
Kyle.

08:43.724 --> 08:45.524
[laughing]

08:45.559 --> 08:47.993
Shouldn't you be on some
fabulous honeymoon right now?

08:48.028 --> 08:49.494
Oh, we leave tonight.

08:49.530 --> 08:51.663
Eight days in Maui.

08:51.698 --> 08:53.198
Ooh, you got room in your
suitcase for one more?

08:53.233 --> 08:54.199
I'll bring the sunscreen.

08:54.234 --> 08:55.100
Already called it.

08:55.135 --> 08:57.035
It's a no-go.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.837
You remember Becca.

08:58.872 --> 08:59.804
Oh yes.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.139
The hopeless romantic.

09:01.174 --> 09:03.108
Aww, you say that almost
like it's a bad thing.

09:03.143 --> 09:04.209
On the contrary.

09:04.244 --> 09:05.176
The maid of honour's job

09:05.212 --> 09:07.045
is to make the happy couple
feel special.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.880
You accomplished it beautifully.

09:08.916 --> 09:10.015
It's a little more than that.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.316
I meant every word.

09:11.351 --> 09:12.217
Even better.

09:12.252 --> 09:14.019
Plays well on camera.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.120
Have fun in Hawaii.

09:15.155 --> 09:16.388
I will.

09:16.423 --> 09:17.389
Aloha.

09:17.424 --> 09:21.493
[laughs]

09:21.528 --> 09:23.061
What about him, Becks?

09:23.096 --> 09:26.364
I mean, he's cute, and
no ring on his finger.

09:26.400 --> 09:27.599
Did you just hear him?

09:27.634 --> 09:30.569
He said "hopeless romantic"
like that's some character flaw.

09:30.604 --> 09:32.137
I don't think he meant it
that way.

09:32.172 --> 09:34.039
He's cute and funny.

09:34.074 --> 09:37.108
He is so not it.

09:38.745 --> 09:40.812
♪

09:40.847 --> 09:43.248
♪<i> Oh, oh, this could be</i>
<i> the start</i> ♪

09:43.283 --> 09:46.585
♪<i> The start of something</i>
<i> beautiful</i> ♪

09:46.620 --> 09:48.820
♪<i> Oh, oh,</i> ♪

09:48.855 --> 09:50.689
♪<i> I hope it never ends,</i> ♪

09:50.724 --> 09:55.994
♪<i> I hope it never ends</i> ♪

09:56.029 --> 10:04.269
♪

10:04.304 --> 10:06.338
[doorbell]

10:17.451 --> 10:20.118
-Craig proposed!
-Craig proposed!

10:20.153 --> 10:22.520
And I needed to stop by
to show you the ring.

10:22.556 --> 10:23.521
Did you help him pick it out?

10:23.557 --> 10:25.423
He asked me where to go,
the rest was all him.

10:25.459 --> 10:27.459
Congratulations, Luce.

10:27.494 --> 10:29.628
Thank you.

10:29.663 --> 10:32.364
So, you know what
I'm going to ask you.

10:32.399 --> 10:34.733
And you know what
I'm going to answer.

10:34.768 --> 10:38.003
You're more than just my cousin,
you're one of my best friends,

10:38.038 --> 10:41.272
and it would make my day if you
would be my Maid of Honour.

10:41.308 --> 10:43.375
Of course I will, Luce.

10:43.410 --> 10:45.443
The venue is only available
June 9th,

10:45.479 --> 10:47.178
so time is short.

10:47.214 --> 10:48.913
And I know things are going
to be crazy with you

10:48.949 --> 10:50.715
taking over the business
around then,

10:50.751 --> 10:52.584
so I promise, I'm not going
to be one of those brides.

10:52.619 --> 10:55.086
I will hold you to that.

10:55.122 --> 10:56.254
I'm getting married!

10:56.289 --> 10:57.389
You're getting married!

10:57.424 --> 10:58.556
And you're finally going
to meet

10:58.592 --> 11:00.892
Craig's college roommate,
Aiden.

11:00.927 --> 11:02.260
He's the best man.

11:02.295 --> 11:04.629
Like, truly "the best" man.

11:04.665 --> 11:06.931
Yes, I'm sure that he is.

11:06.967 --> 11:07.899
Anyway, I have to go.

11:07.934 --> 11:08.900
Craig's waiting in the car.

11:08.935 --> 11:10.568
But I just couldn't wait
to tell you the news.

11:10.604 --> 11:12.904
I am so happy for you.

11:12.939 --> 11:14.906
Please tell Craig hello.

11:14.941 --> 11:16.107
I love you.

11:16.143 --> 11:17.676
Love you, bye!

11:19.646 --> 11:20.645
[sighs]

11:20.681 --> 11:23.615
Well, here we go again.

11:42.169 --> 11:43.168
<i> Hey, Becca.</i>

11:43.203 --> 11:44.335
<i> Good morning.</i>

11:44.371 --> 11:46.071
Oh, morning Becca.

11:46.106 --> 11:47.105
You're here early.

11:47.140 --> 11:48.973
What time is your meeting
with Ingrid Golden?

11:49.009 --> 11:51.409
She should be here any minute.

11:51.445 --> 11:52.477
You know, she's
our biggest client,

11:52.512 --> 11:55.613
and she's so excited to be
working with you now.

11:55.649 --> 11:58.349
Well, I've got some big shoes
to fill with all your accounts.

11:58.385 --> 12:01.653
And I think you both wear
the same exact size.

12:01.688 --> 12:03.321
[laughs]

12:03.356 --> 12:04.189
Did you hear about your cousin?

12:04.224 --> 12:06.324
I did, she paid me a visit
as soon as

12:06.359 --> 12:08.093
the ring was on her finger.

12:08.128 --> 12:11.362
So many happy occasions coming
up in this family, you know?

12:11.398 --> 12:14.199
I mean, Lucie's wedding and
you taking over the business.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.867
Our retirement.

12:15.902 --> 12:18.703
Who wants coffee?

12:18.739 --> 12:20.472
How was Allie's wedding, honey?

12:20.507 --> 12:24.442
You know, it was beautiful,
romantic.

12:24.478 --> 12:26.377
And? Anyone special?

12:26.413 --> 12:29.280
Um, the most adorable
little flower girl.

12:29.316 --> 12:30.281
That's not what I meant.

12:30.317 --> 12:32.684
I'm sure she can decipher
your code, Joyce.

12:32.719 --> 12:35.320
I was a little busy
with Allie.

12:35.355 --> 12:36.554
Don't pester her.

12:36.590 --> 12:39.324
The business is top of her mind
right now, as it should be.

12:39.359 --> 12:41.993
She's waited for this
day forever.

12:42.028 --> 12:43.228
[pointedly]
Oh.

12:43.263 --> 12:44.996
Back to work.

12:45.031 --> 12:46.698
Ingrid, great to see you.

12:46.733 --> 12:47.799
Hi.

12:47.834 --> 12:48.733
Hey, Ingrid.

12:48.769 --> 12:49.868
Hi, Joyce.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.236
-So good to see you again.
-I can't wait to catch up.

12:51.271 --> 12:51.936
Yes.

12:51.972 --> 12:53.037
I will meet you
in my office.

12:53.073 --> 12:54.439
Perfect.

12:56.243 --> 12:58.543
<i> [soft piano jazz]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

12:58.578 --> 13:00.979
Happy engagement party.

13:01.014 --> 13:02.313
Thank you.

13:02.349 --> 13:05.383
Oh, I made you something.

13:05.418 --> 13:08.486
Oh, I love it.

13:08.522 --> 13:10.421
I purposely didn't wear jewelry,
just in case.

13:10.457 --> 13:11.356
[laughs]

13:11.391 --> 13:13.725
Am I that predictable?

13:14.361 --> 13:15.994
You made me send you a picture
of my outfit,

13:16.029 --> 13:18.830
so what other reason
could there be?

13:18.865 --> 13:21.900
Oh, it's perfect.
It's perfect.

13:21.935 --> 13:24.169
You are so good, Becks.

13:24.204 --> 13:27.839
I love it, thank you.

13:27.874 --> 13:29.741
Luce, the caterers have some
questions for us.

13:29.776 --> 13:31.409
Great party, Uncle Paul!

13:31.444 --> 13:32.410
Oh, well.

13:32.445 --> 13:35.013
She's my only daughter,
and I don't mess around.

13:35.048 --> 13:37.215
This is going to be my biggest
production yet.

13:37.250 --> 13:38.416
Oh, he's not kidding.

13:38.451 --> 13:41.519
He wants coverage of every
moment from beginning to end.

13:41.555 --> 13:43.087
Everything's a movie to him.

13:43.123 --> 13:44.122
Well, 10 years from now,

13:44.157 --> 13:45.256
you'll look back
on this moment

13:45.292 --> 13:48.259
and you'll be glad I made
such a big deal out of it.

13:48.295 --> 13:49.594
Come on, they need us
in the kitchen..

13:49.629 --> 13:50.862
Okay.

13:50.897 --> 13:52.697
Try to find Aiden,
the best man.

13:52.732 --> 13:54.599
Go, your dad's waiting.

13:56.102 --> 14:02.207
♪♪

14:04.110 --> 14:08.580
A month later and you still have
impeccable timing.

14:08.615 --> 14:11.549
And I've worked so hard on it
since the last time I saw you.

14:11.585 --> 14:13.051
I do eat real food,

14:13.086 --> 14:15.320
but it seemed a shame to let
these gorgeous cupcakes

14:15.355 --> 14:16.387
go to waste.

14:16.423 --> 14:18.456
Someone put their heart and soul
into making them.

14:18.491 --> 14:19.624
I believe you.

14:19.659 --> 14:22.093
And I believe this was a
selfless effort on your part,

14:22.128 --> 14:22.994
and you did the right thing.

14:23.029 --> 14:25.430
Okay. Let's go with that.

14:25.465 --> 14:26.798
[whispers] I was never here.

14:26.833 --> 14:28.099
[laughs]

14:32.038 --> 14:35.240
And so it's just been me
and Lucie for 16 years.

14:35.275 --> 14:37.242
And though I've produced
blockbusters,

14:37.277 --> 14:41.779
movies on aircraft carriers,
civil war films,

14:41.815 --> 14:44.515
all that is amateur hour
compared to the production

14:44.551 --> 14:47.986
we are making for the wedding
of my only daughter

14:48.021 --> 14:50.922
in just 10 short weeks.

14:50.957 --> 14:54.192
To Lucie and Craig!

14:54.227 --> 14:55.960
(All) To Lucie and Craig!

14:55.996 --> 14:57.028
[glasses clinking]

14:57.063 --> 14:58.730
Cheers.

14:59.966 --> 15:03.301
(whispers) It's so obvious...

15:03.336 --> 15:04.802
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

15:04.838 --> 15:06.004
[laughing]

15:06.039 --> 15:07.438
Becca, this is Aiden.

15:07.474 --> 15:08.673
He came back to town
just in time

15:08.708 --> 15:10.308
to be at my every
beck and call.

15:10.343 --> 15:11.542
[laughs]

15:11.578 --> 15:13.111
Aiden, nice to meet you.

15:13.146 --> 15:14.712
I think we will spend a lot
of time together

15:14.748 --> 15:17.115
doing the bidding
for these two.

15:17.150 --> 15:18.516
It's what I live for.

15:18.551 --> 15:19.217
This guy.

15:19.252 --> 15:21.152
He seriously is the best man.

15:21.187 --> 15:23.788
So I've heard.

15:23.823 --> 15:25.523
Oh, I have to go say hi
to somebody,

15:25.558 --> 15:27.659
but I will leave you two
to get acquainted.

15:27.694 --> 15:29.594
[laughs]

15:30.363 --> 15:31.696
You think he could've been
a little more subtle?

15:31.731 --> 15:34.332
Nope, I don't think
that's in his nature.

15:34.367 --> 15:35.900
Well I gotta say,
I'm not...

15:35.936 --> 15:37.402
I'm not really into
being set up.

15:37.437 --> 15:38.803
I feel the same way.

15:38.838 --> 15:39.871
Right?

15:39.906 --> 15:41.506
Because you feel like you get
all the pressure,

15:41.541 --> 15:42.874
you feel like you're
being interrogated.

15:42.909 --> 15:44.242
The last blind date
I went on,

15:44.277 --> 15:46.544
it felt like a job interview
with a Cobb salad.

15:46.579 --> 15:48.546
[laughs]

15:48.581 --> 15:49.981
Do they really think
we're not onto them, though?

15:50.016 --> 15:51.049
Look at this.

15:51.084 --> 15:52.250
[laughs]

15:52.285 --> 15:54.719
I'm not sure they care
if we are,

15:54.754 --> 15:58.022
but look I think these things
have to happen organically.

15:58.058 --> 15:59.090
I couldn't agree more.

15:59.125 --> 16:00.258
You can't push it.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.193
Okay, well let's just say
we're... we're new friends,

16:02.228 --> 16:05.096
sharing a common responsibility,

16:05.131 --> 16:08.499
and if things develop
from there, then good on us.

16:08.535 --> 16:09.734
I like it.

16:09.769 --> 16:11.836
Sounds like a plan.

16:11.871 --> 16:16.474
<i> [soft piano jazz]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

16:27.620 --> 16:29.020
Hiding out?

16:29.055 --> 16:29.821
It's the shoes.

16:29.856 --> 16:31.356
They're cute,
but they're evil.

16:31.391 --> 16:34.292
I needed a break from them.

16:34.327 --> 16:35.593
So, what's the tally
on setups tonight?

16:35.628 --> 16:36.861
More than the best man?

16:36.896 --> 16:38.062
How do you know
about that?

16:38.098 --> 16:39.464
Oh, please.

16:39.499 --> 16:41.132
The setup was visible
from outer space.

16:41.167 --> 16:43.134
Well, it's unimaginative,

16:43.169 --> 16:45.570
but Lucie and Craig have to work
with what they've got.

16:45.605 --> 16:47.905
Well, maybe that means you get a
little break this time around.

16:47.941 --> 16:49.040
I wouldn't count on it.

16:49.075 --> 16:51.876
They seem pretty committed
to this potential pairing.

16:51.911 --> 16:53.945
Like my uncle said,
tonight's the coming attraction,

16:53.980 --> 16:55.713
the big show's still to come.

16:55.749 --> 16:58.316
I've seen your uncle's movies,
I admire him a lot.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.384
Well, you make films.

16:59.419 --> 17:01.452
It's not every day you get
exposure to a producer.

17:01.488 --> 17:03.154
You should talk to him
about your work.

17:03.189 --> 17:05.823
Yeah, what he does is really not
in my wheelhouse.

17:05.859 --> 17:07.492
I prefer nonfiction all around.

17:07.527 --> 17:08.993
Right. Who needs a script,
right?

17:09.029 --> 17:10.395
Weddings bring
their own drama.

17:10.430 --> 17:11.562
Oh, yes.

17:11.598 --> 17:13.464
Our true selves come out
under heightened circumstances.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.666
A wedding is heightened
times ten.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.268
It's not all dramatic.

17:17.303 --> 17:20.938
I mean, some of it is
a beautiful intensity.

17:20.974 --> 17:23.975
Ah, yes, there's
that romantic side.

17:24.010 --> 17:25.743
[laughs]

17:25.779 --> 17:27.145
If you had seen
what I've seen...

17:27.180 --> 17:29.280
You're talking one day
in the life,

17:29.315 --> 17:30.815
I'm talking the other 364.

17:30.850 --> 17:32.483
Maybe I'm speaking
from personal encounters.

17:32.519 --> 17:34.685
Just because you haven't
experienced true love

17:34.721 --> 17:36.287
doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

17:36.322 --> 17:38.656
Just because you believe in it
doesn't mean it does.

17:38.691 --> 17:39.624
Look, I get it.

17:39.659 --> 17:40.525
Who doesn't want the edited
version of life

17:40.560 --> 17:42.360
where everything works out
in the end?

17:42.395 --> 17:43.828
It's called trust.

17:43.863 --> 17:44.662
Agree to disagree.

17:44.697 --> 17:47.532
I think we've already
arrived there.

17:47.567 --> 17:49.333
Look, I hope I'm wrong.

17:49.369 --> 17:50.301
I know you're wrong.

17:50.336 --> 17:52.370
And you'll have plenty
of chances to prove it.

17:52.405 --> 17:53.971
Maybe even with the best man
out here.

17:54.007 --> 17:57.341
In which case, I will stand
very corrected.

17:57.377 --> 17:58.709
All right then.

17:58.745 --> 18:00.812
See you at the dress fitting
on Monday.

18:00.847 --> 18:02.947
You're coming to
the dress fitting?

18:02.982 --> 18:04.182
Oh, I'm going to be there
for everything

18:04.217 --> 18:05.616
leading up to the big day.

18:05.652 --> 18:07.885
Your uncle is going for quite
the production.

18:07.921 --> 18:09.320
You'll have plenty
of opportunities to try

18:09.355 --> 18:13.324
and show me just how wrong I am
about everything.

18:18.398 --> 18:20.131
And if you send out
the new application now,

18:20.166 --> 18:22.233
I can follow up
after Lucie's fitting.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.602
I should be in by 11:00
at the latest.

18:24.637 --> 18:26.637
<i> Sounds good. And be sure</i>
<i> to send pictures.</i>

18:26.673 --> 18:28.639
Will do, thanks mom.

18:28.675 --> 18:34.045
Symmetrical, classy,
and fit for a bride.

18:39.619 --> 18:40.952
<i> You must be Becca.</i>

18:40.987 --> 18:42.053
<i> We've just gotten started.</i>

18:42.088 --> 18:43.054
<i> Wonderful.</i>

18:44.757 --> 18:47.291
Grams, I'm so sorry
I'm late.

18:47.327 --> 18:48.726
It's been one of those mornings.

18:48.761 --> 18:49.760
Ah, did I miss any dresses?

18:49.796 --> 18:51.095
Still waiting on
the first one.

18:51.131 --> 18:52.964
But I'm not going to cry,
though.

18:52.999 --> 18:54.332
Oh.

18:54.367 --> 18:55.233
Wow!

18:55.268 --> 18:57.368
Hmm-mmm.

19:06.179 --> 19:09.147
Okay, maybe I'm going to cry
just a little bit.

19:09.182 --> 19:11.816
But it's the good kind of cry.

19:11.851 --> 19:13.518
When you see your cousin...

19:13.553 --> 19:14.552
Your granddaughter...

19:14.587 --> 19:17.321
Or yourself in a wedding dress
for the first time.

19:17.357 --> 19:20.658
[laughs]

19:20.693 --> 19:21.726
Aww.

19:23.496 --> 19:25.630
<i> (Kyle) Safe to come back there?</i>
<i> Everybody's decent?</i>

19:25.665 --> 19:27.832
Oh yeah, come on back, Kyle.

19:33.907 --> 19:34.939
Wow.

19:34.974 --> 19:36.107
[giggles]

19:36.142 --> 19:36.908
Beautiful.

19:36.943 --> 19:38.342
You want to give us
a little spin?

19:38.378 --> 19:39.610
Yeah.

19:46.920 --> 19:48.519
Hey.

19:48.555 --> 19:51.189
You know, just because
it's your cousin's turn,

19:51.224 --> 19:53.524
don't let anybody
pressure you.

19:53.560 --> 19:56.327
There's no timeline
on marriage.

19:56.362 --> 19:57.862
I know my time will come.

19:57.897 --> 20:00.164
It's everyone else
who seems to doubt it.

20:00.200 --> 20:01.899
Nobody doubts it.

20:01.935 --> 20:06.204
Well, they sure talk
about it a lot.

20:06.239 --> 20:09.740
I don't know, this one makes me
look hippy.

20:09.776 --> 20:11.375
And I don't mean
like a flower child,

20:11.411 --> 20:13.844
I mean my hips look weird.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.714
Let's try the romantic ball gown
with the spaghetti straps.

20:16.749 --> 20:19.283
Oh, I have a feeling
about that one.

20:21.054 --> 20:22.186
Hello, again.

20:22.222 --> 20:24.055
Grandma Raye, this is Kyle,

20:24.090 --> 20:26.757
Kyle this is Lucie
and my grandmother.

20:26.793 --> 20:27.992
Very nice to meet you.

20:28.027 --> 20:29.360
Nice to meet you too.

20:29.395 --> 20:30.861
How do you know each other?

20:30.897 --> 20:32.363
Uh, we actually met
at another wedding,

20:32.398 --> 20:34.098
and then again at the engagement
party.

20:34.133 --> 20:34.932
Really hit it off.

20:34.968 --> 20:37.201
Very similar philosophies
on life.

20:37.237 --> 20:38.569
You think?

20:38.605 --> 20:40.738
Becca, Lucie's asking
about some jewelry?

20:40.773 --> 20:43.207
Oh, yes, earrings.
I left them in the car.

20:43.243 --> 20:44.242
Oh, okay.

20:51.718 --> 20:54.185
[gasps]

20:54.220 --> 20:55.219
Oh!

20:58.558 --> 21:00.258
This is it.

21:00.293 --> 21:01.626
This is the one.

21:01.661 --> 21:03.594
When you know, you know.

21:03.630 --> 21:05.429
That's how it always happens.

21:05.465 --> 21:07.898
<i> It's perfect.</i>

21:07.934 --> 21:10.868
And...

21:10.903 --> 21:13.137
Oh, they're beautiful.

21:13.172 --> 21:14.238
It's just the earrings to start.

21:14.274 --> 21:17.408
I wanted to see the neckline
before I made the rest.

21:17.443 --> 21:19.277
They're exactly
what I wanted.

21:19.312 --> 21:20.878
And with my hair
in a nice up-do?

21:20.913 --> 21:23.414
That was the inspiration.

21:23.449 --> 21:25.750
Thank you,
they're beautiful.

21:25.785 --> 21:26.984
You made those?

21:27.020 --> 21:27.618
Hmm-mmm.

21:27.654 --> 21:28.452
Do you have a collection?

21:28.488 --> 21:31.055
No, no, I just make them
for myself,

21:31.090 --> 21:32.590
or for friends for gifts.

21:32.625 --> 21:33.457
They're lovely.

21:33.493 --> 21:35.326
If you ever have some
extra pieces,

21:35.361 --> 21:36.961
we like to showcase
new designers here

21:36.996 --> 21:38.229
from time to time.

21:38.264 --> 21:39.163
Do they sell?

21:39.198 --> 21:40.197
Some do, some don't.

21:40.233 --> 21:44.468
But I'm always happy to try
and see how we do.

21:44.504 --> 21:45.569
Sure.

21:45.605 --> 21:49.640
If I ever have some free time,
I'll think about it.

21:49.676 --> 21:54.445
Well, now that I'm set, let's
look at some bridesmaid dresses.

21:54.480 --> 21:56.580
♪♪

21:56.616 --> 21:59.116
Wow. You look like...

21:59.152 --> 22:00.751
Cotton candy?

22:00.787 --> 22:05.656
Well, I was going
to say Cinderella, but...

22:05.692 --> 22:07.158
you know what, let's just try
the next one.

22:07.193 --> 22:08.225
Yeah.

22:10.963 --> 22:14.198
So, does this one come
with instructions?

22:14.233 --> 22:14.932
Oh.

22:14.967 --> 22:15.633
Oh.

22:15.668 --> 22:16.434
Well, it's too big.

22:16.469 --> 22:18.002
Oh, there's another
strap here.

22:18.037 --> 22:18.836
Oh.

22:18.871 --> 22:23.074
[chattering]

22:26.546 --> 22:27.511
[gasps]

22:27.547 --> 22:28.879
Oh, Becca,
that's so...

22:28.915 --> 22:30.014
Blue?

22:30.049 --> 22:32.817
I know, don't you
just love it.

22:32.852 --> 22:33.851
[flatly]
So much.

22:33.886 --> 22:35.986
Besides, you would look good
in a potato sack.

22:36.022 --> 22:36.854
[laughs]

22:36.889 --> 22:38.022
Do you think they have
any of those?

22:38.057 --> 22:39.957
Because I'm pretty sure
I've tried on everything else.

22:39.992 --> 22:43.160
Oh, I think this would
photograph beautifully.

22:43.196 --> 22:44.628
Right, Kyle?

22:44.664 --> 22:45.996
Yeah.

22:46.032 --> 22:48.733
Colour is always good.

22:48.768 --> 22:49.567
See?

22:49.602 --> 22:51.335
Colour is always good.

22:51.371 --> 22:53.871
So, maybe let's try
the yellow.

22:53.906 --> 22:55.506
Yellow?

22:56.876 --> 22:59.210
So you decided on
the yellow dress, huh?

22:59.245 --> 23:01.245
Decided is a relative term.

23:01.280 --> 23:02.146
Lucie chose it.

23:02.181 --> 23:03.681
I didn't want to end
the friendship, so.

23:03.716 --> 23:05.716
Plus, yellow is always nice.

23:05.752 --> 23:06.217
Is it, though?

23:06.252 --> 23:07.351
No, it's terrible.

23:07.387 --> 23:08.285
I look like a banana.

23:08.321 --> 23:10.221
And then there's the whole
straps debate.

23:10.256 --> 23:11.856
Do we wear them up,
do we wear them down?

23:11.891 --> 23:12.423
Uh-huh.

23:12.458 --> 23:13.224
But it's Lucie's day.

23:13.259 --> 23:14.291
You know, I've done
a lot of these.

23:14.327 --> 23:15.593
You're definitely one of
the better maids of honour.

23:15.628 --> 23:18.996
Well, I would go pro,
but then I can't do this
in the Olympics.

23:19.031 --> 23:20.398
No, they let pros
in the Olympics now.

23:20.433 --> 23:21.866
Then I'm going
for the gold!

23:21.901 --> 23:23.367
[laughs]

23:23.403 --> 23:24.402
So, you're a jewelry maker?

23:24.437 --> 23:27.705
No. I am an insurance agent
who makes jewelry.

23:27.740 --> 23:30.541
Or, as my mother likes to say,
I have a little hobby.

23:30.576 --> 23:32.943
Hobbies are usually things
people are bad at.

23:32.979 --> 23:34.412
If they were good,
they'd make it a career.

23:34.447 --> 23:35.713
Maybe it's not about money.

23:35.748 --> 23:37.214
Maybe it's for
the love of it.

23:37.250 --> 23:39.016
For some. For others,
it's about fear.

23:39.051 --> 23:40.050
Excuse me.

23:40.086 --> 23:41.419
I am not afraid.

23:41.454 --> 23:44.455
I didn't say "you,"
I said "others."

23:44.490 --> 23:45.423
But now that you mention it,

23:45.458 --> 23:46.357
you were offered what seemed

23:46.392 --> 23:47.892
like a pretty good opportunity
in there.

23:47.927 --> 23:49.627
It feels like kind of
a no brainer.

23:49.662 --> 23:52.096
I have a lot going on
right now.

23:54.167 --> 23:55.132
You want to know
what I think?

23:55.168 --> 23:58.636
I get the feeling you're
going to tell me anyway.

23:58.671 --> 24:00.271
I think you're an artist,

24:00.306 --> 24:02.373
hiding in the body of
an insurance agent.

24:02.408 --> 24:04.708
And I think you like
to analyze people.

24:04.744 --> 24:05.543
I get it.

24:05.578 --> 24:07.478
Insurance is all
about managing risk.

24:07.513 --> 24:08.712
Making sure that
you're protected

24:08.748 --> 24:10.614
in the event of a disaster,
it's safe.

24:10.650 --> 24:12.817
Being responsible is an asset
to most people.

24:12.852 --> 24:14.718
I didn't say that it wasn't.

24:14.754 --> 24:17.421
Art is unsafe,
it's unpredictable,

24:17.457 --> 24:18.622
it's unconventional.

24:18.658 --> 24:21.659
Exactly, which is why I'm taking
over a successful business

24:21.694 --> 24:23.327
and I make jewelry on the side.

24:23.362 --> 24:24.128
Why?

24:24.163 --> 24:25.129
Why what?

24:25.164 --> 24:26.330
Why do you make jewelry?

24:26.365 --> 24:27.765
Because I love it.

24:27.800 --> 24:31.302
It's challenging,
yet meditative,

24:31.337 --> 24:32.503
and you get to create something

24:32.538 --> 24:34.839
that just exists
in your imagination.

24:34.874 --> 24:36.474
Plus, the perfect piece

24:36.509 --> 24:39.810
makes a person feel like
a million bucks.

24:42.482 --> 24:43.614
You want to know
what I think?

24:43.649 --> 24:44.482
Why do you keep
asking me that?

24:44.517 --> 24:46.684
You're just going
to tell me anyway.

24:46.719 --> 24:49.687
Seeing your face
when you talk about it,

24:49.722 --> 24:54.358
insurance should be
your little hobby,

24:54.393 --> 24:56.594
not the other way around.

24:56.629 --> 24:58.729
See you at the next one.

25:05.304 --> 25:07.505
[jazzy piano music]
♪♪

25:07.540 --> 25:09.473
And then you'll each do
a speech,

25:09.509 --> 25:12.510
well, unless you want to
team up and do one together.

25:12.545 --> 25:14.545
Yeah, since we know you
separately...

25:14.580 --> 25:16.380
We'll each do our own,
right?

25:16.415 --> 25:18.048
Yeah.

25:18.084 --> 25:20.451
Whatever you two want.

25:20.486 --> 25:22.520
Oh, you booked your rooms
at the resort already, right?

25:22.555 --> 25:23.521
Weeks ago.

25:23.556 --> 25:25.956
Don't worry, it's going
to be a perfect wedding.

25:25.992 --> 25:27.858
It's always the perfect wedding
on my watch.

25:27.894 --> 25:29.026
You know, it's a wonder

25:29.061 --> 25:31.395
nobody's made a career out
of the bridesmaid business.

25:31.430 --> 25:33.397
I mean, can you... can
you major in that, or...

25:33.432 --> 25:34.465
[laughs]

25:34.500 --> 25:36.133
Not at my college, but it was
a liberal arts school,

25:36.168 --> 25:38.969
so we could give them time,
it could happen.

25:39.005 --> 25:41.839
So the leap from liberal arts
to insurance?

25:41.874 --> 25:43.407
Actually, art history
to insurance.

25:43.442 --> 25:45.175
Oh, another logical jump.

25:45.211 --> 25:46.744
But with a minor in
business administration,

25:46.779 --> 25:49.079
so it wasn't all art museums
and culture.

25:49.115 --> 25:52.983
There was a Wall Street Journal
subscription in there somewhere.

25:53.019 --> 25:55.085
I did one for me,
and one for my parents,

25:55.121 --> 25:57.154
for the business.

25:57.189 --> 25:58.722
And you said you're taking over
there, soon?

25:58.758 --> 26:01.091
Mmhmm. In July,
just after the wedding.

26:01.127 --> 26:02.393
Oh, wow.

26:02.428 --> 26:03.827
You guys gotta take it easy
on her then,

26:03.863 --> 26:04.995
that's a lot all at once.

26:05.031 --> 26:06.130
[laughs]

26:06.165 --> 26:08.399
I mean, I'm happy to pick up
the wedding slack, though.

26:08.434 --> 26:09.400
You'll show me how, though?

26:09.435 --> 26:10.935
I could write a book.

26:10.970 --> 26:12.202
To the wedding party!

26:12.238 --> 26:13.737
Yes, to the wedding party.

26:13.773 --> 26:14.705
Cheers.

26:14.740 --> 26:16.840
Cheers.

26:18.411 --> 26:21.712
♪<i> I just want to shine,</i> ♪

26:21.747 --> 26:23.781
♪<i> show the world just</i>
<i> what I'm made of</i> ♪

26:23.816 --> 26:25.883
♪<i> What are we afraid of</i> ♪

26:25.918 --> 26:28.018
♪<i> I just want to shi-ii-ine</i> ♪

26:28.054 --> 26:29.787
[doorbell rings]

26:29.822 --> 26:33.657
♪<i> I just want to shi-ine</i> ♪

26:33.693 --> 26:37.461
♪<i> Even when it rains</i>
<i> a bit outside</i> ♪

26:37.496 --> 26:38.862
♪<i> I want to shine</i> ♪

26:38.898 --> 26:40.130
Hi, Mom.

26:40.166 --> 26:41.799
Hi, sweetie.

26:41.834 --> 26:45.836
Sorry to stop in like this,
but I have a surprise for you.

26:45.871 --> 26:48.072
A surprise?

26:48.107 --> 26:49.740
It's the contract.

26:49.775 --> 26:52.376
It doesn't go into effect
for another six weeks,

26:52.411 --> 26:54.178
but it's all ready for us
to sign.

26:54.213 --> 26:56.013
We wanted to give you plenty
of time to read through it.

26:56.048 --> 26:58.082
I know there's a lot going on
right now

26:58.117 --> 26:59.917
with your cousin's wedding
coming up.

26:59.952 --> 27:00.884
Are you happy?

27:00.920 --> 27:01.752
Yes!

27:01.787 --> 27:03.187
Because your reaction
to the papers

27:03.222 --> 27:04.588
isn't quite what I expected.

27:04.624 --> 27:06.724
Just a bit overwhelming,
that's all.

27:06.759 --> 27:08.058
Okay.

27:08.094 --> 27:09.093
I love our business.

27:09.128 --> 27:10.728
I love what our family built.

27:10.763 --> 27:11.695
I just want to make sure.

27:11.731 --> 27:14.531
I'm going to make you and Dad
very proud.

27:14.567 --> 27:17.368
Becca, always.

27:17.403 --> 27:18.602
All right, let's get
some coffee.

27:18.638 --> 27:19.870
Okay, sounds good.

27:19.905 --> 27:20.738
[giggles]

27:35.054 --> 27:36.253
Kyle.

27:36.288 --> 27:37.721
Ah, there she is.

27:37.757 --> 27:38.922
Lucie isn't here yet,

27:38.958 --> 27:40.557
I was over at the tux shop
with Craig and the groomsmen,

27:40.593 --> 27:43.193
but I figured this
was more important.

27:43.229 --> 27:45.062
Don't tell anybody
that I said this,

27:45.097 --> 27:47.398
[whispers] the wedding day
is really about the bride.

27:47.433 --> 27:48.599
You're telling me.

27:48.634 --> 27:50.768
This is my third wedding
just this year.

27:50.803 --> 27:52.369
Huh, it's my 23rd.

27:52.405 --> 27:54.438
Wow. You are in demand.

27:54.473 --> 27:55.706
Don't believe in doing
anything halfway.

27:55.741 --> 27:57.508
Really.

27:58.344 --> 27:59.009
What?

27:59.045 --> 28:01.979
You keep love at arm's length.

28:02.014 --> 28:04.114
[laughs]

28:04.150 --> 28:06.583
It's not like I don't date.

28:06.619 --> 28:08.085
Besides, unlike you,

28:08.120 --> 28:10.954
I didn't exactly have stellar
parental role models.

28:10.990 --> 28:14.491
So, how do you make such
beautiful wedding videos?

28:14.527 --> 28:16.427
I saw Allie and Dan's.

28:16.462 --> 28:19.129
Storytelling is my passion.

28:19.165 --> 28:20.731
So, tell me about
the other films,

28:20.766 --> 28:22.399
not the love stories
where you have

28:22.435 --> 28:25.302
to edit out the messy stuff.

28:25.337 --> 28:28.439
I like to shine a light
on things that don't get
enough attention.

28:28.474 --> 28:30.307
Use my films to inspire.

28:30.342 --> 28:32.509
Like what?

28:32.545 --> 28:33.510
You really want to know?

28:33.546 --> 28:35.512
Yes, I really want to know.

28:35.548 --> 28:36.780
All right.

28:36.816 --> 28:38.415
Meet me at the editing
bay tomorrow.

28:38.451 --> 28:39.483
I'll text you the address.

28:39.518 --> 28:41.952
You can get away
from "insurance."

28:41.987 --> 28:42.886
[laughs]

28:42.922 --> 28:44.788
You say insurance
like it's a bad thing.

28:44.824 --> 28:46.290
Not bad, per se.

28:46.325 --> 28:47.791
But maybe I'm shining a light
on something else

28:47.827 --> 28:49.259
that needs your attention.

28:49.295 --> 28:51.161
Hi. Sorry I'm late,
did I miss anything?

28:51.197 --> 28:52.362
(Both) No.

28:52.398 --> 28:53.464
Here are the cakes.

28:53.499 --> 28:54.465
Cake, cake.

28:54.500 --> 28:55.666
That's a lot of cake.

28:55.701 --> 28:56.567
[laughs]

29:04.477 --> 29:05.476
Nice digs.

29:05.511 --> 29:06.343
[laughs]

29:06.378 --> 29:07.878
Not what I expected.

29:07.913 --> 29:09.279
Yeah, I got a little deal
with the station.

29:09.315 --> 29:10.814
I do some freelance work
for them,

29:10.850 --> 29:13.117
and they let me
use their equipment.

29:13.152 --> 29:15.185
So, this is not
a wedding video.

29:15.221 --> 29:17.354
This is not a wedding video.

29:17.389 --> 29:21.125
Um. Uh, this is Staff Sergeant
Adam Wiley, and Emra,

29:21.160 --> 29:23.660
who incidentally,
outranks him.

29:23.696 --> 29:25.863
A little known fact, a military
dog is always

29:25.898 --> 29:28.499
one rank higher than
its fellow servicemen.

29:28.534 --> 29:30.667
It's considered
a sign of respect.

29:30.703 --> 29:32.469
As it should be.

29:32.505 --> 29:35.973
So, what are you shining
a light on here?

29:36.008 --> 29:37.007
My mother.

29:37.042 --> 29:41.211
Um, this is her, and this
is her pet project,

29:41.247 --> 29:43.380
pun definitely intended.

29:43.415 --> 29:45.315
She was in the military,
and now that she's retired,

29:45.351 --> 29:48.018
she works with American Humane
to reunite soldiers

29:48.053 --> 29:51.355
with the dogs with
whom they served.

29:51.390 --> 29:53.056
I love this.

29:53.092 --> 29:54.925
You want to talk about love?

29:54.960 --> 29:55.993
Man's best friend.

29:56.028 --> 29:57.027
These dogs save lives.

29:57.062 --> 29:57.995
Literally.

29:58.030 --> 29:59.229
Figuratively.

29:59.265 --> 30:00.597
This means something.

30:00.633 --> 30:02.599
Well, your wedding videos
mean something too.

30:02.635 --> 30:04.101
Maybe not as much to you,

30:04.136 --> 30:06.336
but you're giving people
a huge gift.

30:06.372 --> 30:09.273
Yeah, but I feel like this could
be my ticket.

30:09.308 --> 30:11.175
Has your mom seen it yet?

30:11.210 --> 30:13.076
Uh, I want to wait
till it's ready.

30:13.112 --> 30:14.211
But I get to see it today.

30:14.246 --> 30:16.113
A few clips.

30:16.148 --> 30:18.549
This is my calling card,
I gotta get it right.

30:18.584 --> 30:21.518
Sounds like that might be
a little fear talking.

30:21.554 --> 30:24.188
What, you can dish it,
but you can't take it?

30:24.223 --> 30:25.222
Let's get a coffee.

30:25.257 --> 30:26.957
[laughs]

30:26.992 --> 30:29.860
Fact is, I put a film out there
once before it was ready,

30:29.895 --> 30:32.896
and that film is sitting in
a drawer in my apartment.

30:32.932 --> 30:34.431
Well, I don't know
about your other films,

30:34.466 --> 30:36.133
but this one sounds special.

30:36.168 --> 30:38.402
Not only because of your mother
who sounds incredible,

30:38.437 --> 30:41.104
but it's a reminder of the good
that exists in our world,

30:41.140 --> 30:42.272
and we need that.

30:42.308 --> 30:45.342
But you have to put it
out there.

30:47.313 --> 30:49.279
I will finish editing
by the time we leave

30:49.315 --> 30:50.480
for Lucie's wedding weekend.

30:50.516 --> 30:53.483
That gives me a few weeks.

30:53.519 --> 30:54.484
Now, what about you?

30:54.520 --> 30:55.152
What about me?

30:55.187 --> 30:56.553
This isn't a one-sided deal.

30:56.589 --> 30:58.222
This isn't a deal at all.

30:58.257 --> 30:59.723
Oh, it's a deal now.

30:59.758 --> 31:02.159
Better practice
what you preach.

31:02.194 --> 31:04.728
Make a few pieces, put them
in the bridal shop.

31:04.763 --> 31:05.896
What if they don't sell?

31:05.931 --> 31:07.598
So what if they don't.

31:07.633 --> 31:08.599
You're re-gifting them
to a friend,

31:08.634 --> 31:10.133
what are you out,
some time and some beads?

31:10.169 --> 31:13.136
I don't use beads, I use
crystals and gemstones,

31:13.172 --> 31:15.205
I run a classy operation here.

31:17.276 --> 31:18.642
You can look at it as another
great opportunity

31:18.677 --> 31:19.743
to prove how wrong I am.

31:19.778 --> 31:22.446
Now that does intrigue me some.

31:22.481 --> 31:24.815
Do we have a deal?

31:24.850 --> 31:27.384
Okay, you got a deal.

31:31.824 --> 31:33.790
And please tell the Hankmans
I'm so sorry I had

31:33.826 --> 31:35.993
to move their appointment today,
something came up,

31:36.028 --> 31:39.429
but I am all set
for 3:30 tomorrow.

31:39.465 --> 31:40.697
And check back in with
the Eddingers

31:40.733 --> 31:43.367
on their life insurance policy,
we haven't heard back from them,

31:43.402 --> 31:46.103
and we still have to schedule
a physical.

31:46.138 --> 31:47.070
Okay, great.

31:47.106 --> 31:49.539
Well, let me know if anything
else comes up.

31:49.575 --> 31:51.942
All right, bye.

31:51.977 --> 31:53.010
[sighs]

31:53.045 --> 31:54.278
The epitome
of multitasking.

31:54.313 --> 31:56.947
You have no idea, but I promised
the bridal store that I would

31:56.982 --> 31:59.983
get the collection to them by
your fitting this afternoon.

32:00.019 --> 32:04.221
So, what changed your mind
about selling your work?

32:04.256 --> 32:07.324
I guess I just wanted to see
how I'd do,

32:07.359 --> 32:08.725
I didn't want to have any
"what ifs."

32:08.761 --> 32:11.194
And I cannot thank you both
enough for helping me.

32:11.230 --> 32:13.230
Oh, of course we'd
show up for you.

32:13.265 --> 32:14.865
You always show up for us.

32:14.900 --> 32:16.066
Just wait until your wedding.

32:16.101 --> 32:17.401
The payback you've
got coming...

32:17.436 --> 32:18.068
[laughs]

32:18.103 --> 32:19.670
Is gonna be off the charts.

32:19.705 --> 32:21.305
As soon as you find
the guy.

32:21.340 --> 32:25.142
Okay, enough of this talk.
I gotta finish soldering.

32:28.881 --> 32:30.714
(whispers) These are gorgeous.

32:32.117 --> 32:35.419
I think the bodice fits
much better now, Luce.

32:35.454 --> 32:37.187
Mmhmm.

32:37.222 --> 32:40.490
Your mother would be
so proud.

32:40.526 --> 32:43.360
I just wish she could
be here to see this day.

32:43.395 --> 32:44.928
Me too.

32:44.964 --> 32:48.365
But this is a happy time,
so we're going to be happy.

32:48.400 --> 32:49.900
[door bells jingle]

32:49.935 --> 32:52.135
As promised...

32:54.473 --> 32:57.708
<i> Becca, these are gorgeous.</i>

32:57.743 --> 33:00.377
I'll put them out today,
and we'll see how we do.

33:00.412 --> 33:01.278
Thank you.

33:01.313 --> 33:02.813
You're welcome.

33:04.416 --> 33:05.582
Hi.

33:05.617 --> 33:07.384
Honey, are you okay?

33:07.419 --> 33:08.719
You seem tired.

33:08.754 --> 33:09.653
No, I'm good.

33:09.688 --> 33:12.122
It's just, it's a lot
with the wedding,

33:12.157 --> 33:14.291
and learning to manage
the business.

33:14.326 --> 33:20.197
Becca, you have the habit of
putting everyone else first.

33:20.232 --> 33:24.067
It's your best quality
and your biggest flaw.

33:24.103 --> 33:26.470
I do hope you're taking time
for you.

33:26.505 --> 33:27.604
I am.

33:27.639 --> 33:29.439
I promise.

33:35.781 --> 33:39.983
Oh, the greatest part is
the signing on the dotted line.

33:40.019 --> 33:43.487
New business, and
it's a big contract.

33:43.522 --> 33:44.254
Yeah.

33:44.289 --> 33:45.255
Feels great.

33:45.290 --> 33:47.924
[phone rings]

33:47.960 --> 33:48.759
Hello?

33:48.794 --> 33:50.093
<i> Becca?</i>

33:50.129 --> 33:50.894
Luce?

33:50.929 --> 33:52.662
Hey, I'm in a meeting
with my mom.

33:52.698 --> 33:53.563
Hi, Luce.

33:53.599 --> 33:55.065
Hi, Aunt Joyce.

33:55.100 --> 33:56.099
I am so glad you answered,
Becks.

33:56.135 --> 33:59.803
Craig has food poisoning,
and we're in the ER.

33:59.838 --> 34:01.772
Ooh, is he okay?

34:01.807 --> 34:03.240
He's going to be fine, however,

34:03.275 --> 34:04.941
he's hooked up to
an IV right now,

34:04.977 --> 34:06.643
and we're supposed to be
on our way to the inn

34:06.678 --> 34:08.512
for our food tasting
this afternoon.

34:08.547 --> 34:11.148
Can you cover for me?
Please?

34:11.183 --> 34:12.816
I'm at work.

34:12.851 --> 34:14.785
Aunt Joyce, can Becca
please save my life

34:14.820 --> 34:16.353
and take the rest
of the day off?

34:16.388 --> 34:18.255
<i> Or else we'll all be eating</i>
<i> boxed mac and cheese</i>

34:18.290 --> 34:19.222
<i> at my wedding,</i>

34:19.258 --> 34:21.525
And Becca, you'll have
to help me cook it.

34:21.560 --> 34:23.593
Yeah, I really don't think
it's going to come to that.

34:23.629 --> 34:25.996
Of course she can go.

34:26.031 --> 34:28.331
<i> And tell Craig that we all hope</i>
<i> he feels better soon.</i>

34:28.367 --> 34:29.499
Thanks, Aunt Joyce.

34:29.535 --> 34:30.967
Will do.

34:36.575 --> 34:37.107
Kyle.

34:37.142 --> 34:38.141
What are you doing here?

34:38.177 --> 34:40.710
Uh, Lucie told me that
you were standing in for her

34:40.746 --> 34:41.678
at the food tasting,

34:41.713 --> 34:43.480
and it seemed kind of silly
to take two cars.

34:43.515 --> 34:44.481
I parked just around
the corner.

34:44.516 --> 34:45.515
Why are you even going?

34:45.551 --> 34:47.384
The bride and groom
aren't going to be there.

34:47.419 --> 34:49.352
It's all part of the story.

34:49.388 --> 34:51.621
I never want to miss an
opportunity to see you eating.

34:51.657 --> 34:53.657
So I've noticed.

34:54.993 --> 34:55.859
Your folks were okay

34:55.894 --> 34:56.927
with you leaving in
the middle of the day?

34:56.962 --> 34:59.529
Family comes first,
business is a close second.

34:59.565 --> 35:00.797
No siblings to pick up
the slack?

35:00.833 --> 35:02.032
Nope. It's just me.

35:02.067 --> 35:03.834
Ah, the only child.

35:03.869 --> 35:04.901
Great hope of the family.

35:04.937 --> 35:05.902
I know that well.

35:05.938 --> 35:06.703
You too?

35:06.738 --> 35:07.704
Oh, yep.

35:07.739 --> 35:09.739
I may not be able to carry on
the Foster name,

35:09.775 --> 35:11.308
but the legacy's
on my shoulders.

35:11.343 --> 35:12.175
I get it.

35:12.211 --> 35:14.511
I wanted a sibling
for that very reason.

35:14.546 --> 35:16.046
Also, to blame things
on when I broke stuff.

35:16.081 --> 35:17.247
[laughs]

35:17.282 --> 35:19.249
I felt the same way.

35:19.284 --> 35:20.717
Wait, are we...

35:20.752 --> 35:22.052
Are we agreeing on something?

35:22.087 --> 35:23.353
Yeah, I think we are.

35:23.388 --> 35:24.154
Weird.

35:24.189 --> 35:24.921
It feels strange.

35:24.957 --> 35:25.489
Does.

35:25.524 --> 35:27.657
Don't get used to it.

35:51.116 --> 35:52.749
Why don't you just call her

35:52.784 --> 35:54.651
and ask if they've sold
any of your stuff?

35:54.686 --> 35:56.153
She told me she would
let me know,

35:56.188 --> 35:57.487
and I don't want to bother her.

35:57.523 --> 35:59.289
It's only been three days.

35:59.324 --> 36:00.323
Maybe you don't want
to know the answer.

36:00.359 --> 36:04.027
I want to know the answer
if the answer is good.

36:04.062 --> 36:05.028
Okay, you're right.

36:05.063 --> 36:06.096
It's fear.

36:06.131 --> 36:08.532
Look, there's never been
a question what I would do

36:08.567 --> 36:11.168
with my life, this
was always the plan,

36:11.203 --> 36:12.769
and I don't want to know
the answer,

36:12.804 --> 36:15.539
because now it feels like
there's a question mark

36:15.574 --> 36:18.642
after everything, and that could
come with a lot of changes.

36:18.677 --> 36:21.511
It's like we talked about,
art is unsafe.

36:21.547 --> 36:23.747
That's what makes it exciting.

36:26.084 --> 36:27.651
Well, what about you?

36:27.686 --> 36:29.186
How's the editing going?

36:29.221 --> 36:31.288
[groans]

36:31.323 --> 36:32.522
It's a lot easier
to churn them out

36:32.558 --> 36:34.391
when you're not
personally invested.

36:34.426 --> 36:36.459
So why do you want
to tell this story?

36:38.230 --> 36:43.333
Well, um, my Mom is
an incredible woman.

36:43.368 --> 36:46.069
You know, after my father left,
she picked herself up,

36:46.104 --> 36:49.873
she raised a kid on her own,
served her country.

36:49.908 --> 36:53.677
I guess this is my way
of honouring that.

36:53.712 --> 36:55.912
I understand why it means
so much to you,

36:55.948 --> 36:58.648
but in my experience,
our work is never finished.

36:58.684 --> 37:01.017
We just stop adding beads.

37:01.053 --> 37:01.885
I thought you didn't use beads.

37:01.920 --> 37:04.154
Sometimes you need them
for a metaphor.

37:04.189 --> 37:04.988
[chuckles]

37:05.023 --> 37:06.423
Becca!

37:06.458 --> 37:08.925
Aiden, hey, it's good
to see you.

37:08.961 --> 37:12.195
I got a message that the, uh,
the groom is incapacitated,

37:12.231 --> 37:13.930
and I was to report
for duty with you.

37:13.966 --> 37:15.699
So, here I am.

37:15.734 --> 37:16.866
Rearranged my day.

37:16.902 --> 37:18.668
[laughs]

37:18.704 --> 37:20.537
Mmm. Do you know where
we're supposed to go?

37:20.572 --> 37:21.538
So sorry.

37:21.573 --> 37:22.672
Um, Kyle, videographer.

37:22.708 --> 37:25.075
This is Aiden,
Best Man.

37:27.479 --> 37:28.778
Seen you on film.

37:28.814 --> 37:30.413
Yeah, and I... I saw you
at the, uh,

37:30.449 --> 37:31.114
the engagement party.

37:31.149 --> 37:32.415
Nice to meet you,
officially.

37:32.451 --> 37:33.316
Yeah.

37:34.820 --> 37:36.453
Uh, I'm gonna go set up.

37:36.488 --> 37:37.754
Okay.

37:40.459 --> 37:41.625
<i> Mmm!</i>

37:41.660 --> 37:42.192
<i> Oh.</i>

37:42.227 --> 37:43.360
Mmm!

37:43.395 --> 37:44.094
Hey-

37:44.129 --> 37:45.128
That is so good.

37:45.163 --> 37:46.463
You need to share some
of that salmon, you know.

37:46.498 --> 37:47.264
Thank you so much.

37:47.299 --> 37:48.198
Thank you.

37:48.233 --> 37:49.332
It's really good.

37:49.368 --> 37:50.800
Do you think they would give us
another if we tell them

37:50.836 --> 37:51.935
we're not sure yet?

37:51.970 --> 37:53.536
<i> It's worth a shot.</i>

37:53.572 --> 37:54.738
Although I'm moving into
the chicken.

37:54.773 --> 37:56.039
Do you want to try
some of this?

37:56.074 --> 37:57.140
No. I'm fine.

37:57.175 --> 37:59.042
Just here to capture the magic.

37:59.077 --> 38:01.444
You know what you have to try
is this garlic mashed potato.

38:01.480 --> 38:03.513
That might be the best
I've ever had.

38:04.349 --> 38:05.315
-Wow!
-Right?

38:05.350 --> 38:06.249
That's amazing.

38:06.285 --> 38:07.083
<i> What is this sauce?</i>

38:07.119 --> 38:08.318
<i> I have no idea,</i>
<i> but it's butter.</i>

38:08.353 --> 38:09.419
Yeah, but there's truff...

38:09.454 --> 38:10.720
<i> Truffle oil, right?</i>

38:10.756 --> 38:12.088
<i> Yeah, there's definitely</i>
<i> truffle in there.</i>

38:12.124 --> 38:13.657
Sorry. Sorry, sorry.

38:13.692 --> 38:14.891
You know what I would like?

38:14.926 --> 38:17.294
I'd like to get a shot
of that chicken.

38:17.329 --> 38:18.161
That does look good.

38:18.196 --> 38:18.995
-Chicken?
-Yeah.

38:19.031 --> 38:19.963
Before we eat...

38:19.998 --> 38:21.398
Yeah. Could you move
over just a little bit?

38:21.433 --> 38:23.266
Oh Just a-

38:23.302 --> 38:25.268
Sorry, you know what?

38:25.304 --> 38:27.270
Let's get the chair right out
of there, actually.

38:27.306 --> 38:28.104
The whole chair?

38:28.140 --> 38:30.740
Yeah, just get
the whole chair out.

38:30.776 --> 38:31.441
All right.

38:31.476 --> 38:32.942
Yeah, there you...

38:32.978 --> 38:33.643
Like this.

38:33.679 --> 38:34.377
Yeah.

38:34.413 --> 38:35.512
Actually, you know,
why don't I?

38:35.547 --> 38:36.613
Look at that,
look at that.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.248
Why don't I scooch
over here.

38:38.283 --> 38:40.917
There, now you've got a clear
shot of all that delicious food?

38:40.952 --> 38:41.851
See? Perfect.

38:41.887 --> 38:44.254
That is better.
That's definitely better.

38:44.289 --> 38:46.756
<i> That's great, yeah.</i>
<i> Beautiful.</i>

38:46.792 --> 38:47.857
Oh, and the shrimp
is all you.

38:47.893 --> 38:48.725
I'm allergic.

38:48.760 --> 38:49.459
Oh, should we have them
take that away?

38:49.494 --> 38:50.360
I know that can
be dangerous.

38:50.395 --> 38:52.162
No, no, no, no.
No. It's not that bad.

38:52.197 --> 38:53.196
I just get hives,
that's all.

38:53.231 --> 38:53.997
No fun.

38:54.032 --> 38:55.532
Yeah.

38:55.567 --> 38:57.534
Um, let's do this.

38:57.569 --> 38:59.369
Look, I'm just going to do
a clean shot of the shrimp,

38:59.404 --> 39:00.537
just with Becca
and the shrimp.

39:00.572 --> 39:02.305
Okay?

39:02.341 --> 39:03.540
Do I smile?

39:03.575 --> 39:04.607
<i> Great idea.</i>

39:05.911 --> 39:07.577
He's thorough.

39:10.649 --> 39:12.649
[chuckles]

39:13.552 --> 39:17.787
No, I'm not taking that offer
back to my client.

39:17.823 --> 39:19.489
Look, if you think you can play
usual games with us,

39:19.524 --> 39:22.025
you're sorely mistaken.

39:22.060 --> 39:23.727
No.

39:23.762 --> 39:25.662
He seems... uh... smart.

39:25.697 --> 39:26.363
He's a nice guy.

39:26.398 --> 39:28.531
Yeah. Bit of a shark, though.

39:28.567 --> 39:30.700
If I ever need a lawyer,
I know who to call.

39:30.736 --> 39:33.036
[birds chirping]

39:33.071 --> 39:35.205
Wow. You know, I should grab
some establishing shots

39:35.240 --> 39:36.439
of this place for the video.

39:36.475 --> 39:38.742
We're going to be here for three
days on the wedding weekend.

39:38.777 --> 39:40.377
Yeah, but I have to follow
the bride around.

39:40.412 --> 39:42.245
Lucie is not going to be one
of those brides,

39:42.280 --> 39:43.713
she has promised.

39:43.749 --> 39:44.848
They all promise.

39:44.883 --> 39:46.015
[laughs]

39:46.051 --> 39:47.817
You want to come with?

39:48.420 --> 39:49.586
Don't insult me,
Andrew.

39:49.621 --> 39:51.654
Yes.

39:51.690 --> 39:53.823
Very much.

39:56.361 --> 39:59.195
So how is it you've been
a bridesmaid nine times,

39:59.231 --> 40:00.096
and never a bride?

40:00.132 --> 40:02.031
Soon to be ten times.

40:02.067 --> 40:03.867
That's a lot of dresses
you'll never wear again.

40:03.902 --> 40:04.868
One was a pantsuit.

40:04.903 --> 40:05.935
I could open up a shop,

40:05.971 --> 40:07.404
rent 'em out for
special occasions.

40:07.439 --> 40:09.305
[laughs]

40:12.144 --> 40:15.211
Everyone I know has
this magical story

40:15.247 --> 40:16.880
when it comes to love.

40:16.915 --> 40:18.114
They just knew.

40:18.150 --> 40:20.550
And that's what you want?

40:20.585 --> 40:23.887
My last boyfriend, Dylan,
he was a wonderful guy,

40:23.922 --> 40:26.723
and everything
was perfectly fine.

40:26.758 --> 40:28.558
He was ready to get married.

40:28.593 --> 40:30.427
So, what happened?

40:30.462 --> 40:32.729
He wanted more than
just perfectly fine,

40:32.764 --> 40:33.863
and he deserved that, too.

40:33.899 --> 40:39.269
I don't think it's unreasonable
to want to be sure.

40:39.304 --> 40:41.271
In my experience, everybody
has a magical story

40:41.306 --> 40:42.472
for the interview.

40:42.507 --> 40:44.641
And then you delve deeper, and
you see that we're just really

40:44.676 --> 40:47.377
good at rewriting the fairy tale
into our history.

40:47.412 --> 40:50.647
You still don't believe
in that kind of love.

40:50.682 --> 40:51.881
I don't know.

40:51.917 --> 40:54.451
I thought that I had defied
the odds of my parents' divorce

40:54.486 --> 40:57.754
when I met my ex-girlfriend,
Ellie.

40:57.789 --> 40:59.456
We had that instant
connection thing,

40:59.491 --> 41:02.959
she was the one, and she was
on the same page.

41:02.994 --> 41:05.261
So, what happened?

41:05.297 --> 41:06.963
Page turned for her.

41:06.998 --> 41:08.965
It's funny how you can be
so sure about something,

41:09.000 --> 41:10.233
and so wrong.

41:10.268 --> 41:11.468
Hmm.

41:11.503 --> 41:14.571
It must've been so hard.

41:14.606 --> 41:19.075
But you can't shut down just
because of one experience.

41:19.110 --> 41:20.243
And if you spend all your energy

41:20.278 --> 41:21.644
looking for something
so specific,

41:21.680 --> 41:26.449
you might not recognize it
when it arrives.

41:26.485 --> 41:30.220
<i> Becca. Time to taste</i>
<i> the appetizers.</i>

41:34.726 --> 41:36.326
Shall we?

41:36.361 --> 41:37.393
Mmm.

41:43.535 --> 41:46.870
That was a beautiful...

41:46.905 --> 41:47.871
[phone rings]

41:47.906 --> 41:48.905
Hello?

41:48.940 --> 41:51.508
<i> Hi Becca, it's Holly</i>
<i> from the bridal shop.</i>

41:51.543 --> 41:52.342
Hi Holly.

41:52.377 --> 41:54.310
So, I've been meaning
to call you,

41:54.346 --> 41:55.845
but we've been so busy.

41:55.881 --> 41:57.213
We've been swamped.

41:57.249 --> 42:01.017
<i> So we sold out</i>
<i> in three days.</i>

42:01.052 --> 42:03.953
<i> I'm sending a cheque</i>
<i> for the first pieces.</i>

42:03.989 --> 42:06.523
Wait, well that's amazing!

42:06.558 --> 42:09.325
Um, I... I don't even know
what to say.

42:09.361 --> 42:10.994
Say you'll make more for us.

42:11.029 --> 42:14.297
<i> And I've told our jewelry</i>
<i> distributor about you.</i>

42:14.332 --> 42:17.667
If she likes your work,
you're on your way.

42:17.702 --> 42:18.568
Really?

42:18.603 --> 42:20.537
But she needs to see
a full collection,

42:20.572 --> 42:22.572
none of this "assorted pieces"
business.

42:22.607 --> 42:24.574
<i> She wants to know</i>
<i> you got the goods.</i>

42:24.609 --> 42:26.843
Absolutely, I will get
right to work.

42:26.878 --> 42:29.178
Thank you so much.

42:29.214 --> 42:30.413
We'll be in touch.

42:30.448 --> 42:31.314
<i> Bye.</i>

42:33.084 --> 42:34.484
[screams excitedly]

42:34.519 --> 42:38.054
[laughs]

42:38.089 --> 42:38.855
Looks like that question mark

42:38.890 --> 42:40.356
just became an
exclamation point.

42:40.392 --> 42:43.293
Maybe I can do both.

42:46.531 --> 42:49.499
Well, here's a subject
I'm really going to miss
on the golf course

42:49.534 --> 42:51.834
a few short weeks from now.

42:51.870 --> 42:53.570
Aggregate cost payments.

42:53.605 --> 42:54.604
[crowd laughs]

42:54.639 --> 42:56.139
But he's going to miss
you all.

42:56.174 --> 42:57.840
Really, we both will.

42:57.876 --> 43:00.276
And thankfully, we're leaving
you in the best hands

43:00.312 --> 43:02.612
imaginable, Becca.

43:02.647 --> 43:05.982
[applause]

43:06.017 --> 43:07.483
[whispers] Have you signed yet?

43:07.519 --> 43:09.919
[whispers] Uh, no.
I'm still reading it.

43:09.955 --> 43:11.087
You've gotta sign by next week.

43:11.122 --> 43:14.023
That's the day we've put
in the contract.

43:14.059 --> 43:18.361
<i> The per currents limit states</i>
<i> the maximum benefit available..</i>

43:18.396 --> 43:27.337
♪

43:27.372 --> 43:36.312
♪

43:36.348 --> 43:40.216
You might be my best one yet.

43:40.251 --> 43:41.184
With a higher deductible,

43:41.219 --> 43:44.287
you will pay less on
your monthly premiums.

43:44.322 --> 43:49.459
[drilling sound]

43:49.494 --> 43:51.461
No, that sounds great.

43:51.496 --> 43:53.329
[chuckles]

43:56.534 --> 43:57.800
Are we keeping you awake?

43:57.836 --> 43:59.535
No, no, I'm good.

43:59.571 --> 44:01.638
I just, uh, there's
just a lot going on.

44:01.673 --> 44:04.040
I'm learning the payroll
system at work,

44:04.075 --> 44:05.408
which is a laugh riot,

44:05.443 --> 44:07.644
and doing the bidding
of this one here.

44:07.679 --> 44:08.845
Oh no.

44:08.880 --> 44:10.546
Am I one of those brides?

44:10.582 --> 44:11.781
I so wasn't going to be.

44:11.816 --> 44:16.252
No, you are great, and this
weekend is going to be perfect.

44:16.287 --> 44:18.588
Come on, Becks, we know you.

44:18.623 --> 44:20.890
What's going on?

44:20.925 --> 44:22.492
Okay, um...

44:22.527 --> 44:27.397
I'm making a collection
for a jewelry distributor.

44:27.432 --> 44:29.265
Holly from the bridal
shop introduced me,

44:29.300 --> 44:30.466
and I need to finish it tonight

44:30.502 --> 44:33.603
so I can get it to Holly before
we leave for the wedding.

44:33.638 --> 44:35.705
So, you're not taking over
the company?

44:35.740 --> 44:37.407
No, I am.

44:37.442 --> 44:39.709
I'm gonna do both.

44:39.744 --> 44:43.513
I'm gonna be delicate here,
because we're family.

44:43.548 --> 44:45.715
But if this is what doing both
looks like

44:45.750 --> 44:47.717
before you've even signed
those papers...

44:47.752 --> 44:48.885
Look, my business,

44:48.920 --> 44:50.119
it's always going
to come first,

44:50.155 --> 44:53.523
but I don't even know if she's
going to like my collection.

44:53.558 --> 44:57.293
If you think you can manage it,
we're behind you 100 percent.

44:57.328 --> 44:58.761
Thank you guys.

44:58.797 --> 45:00.029
All right, I should get going.

45:00.065 --> 45:01.097
I have a bunch of calls to make,

45:01.132 --> 45:04.467
I have to send in a policy
and finish a collection.

45:04.502 --> 45:06.969
And I will see you soon.

45:07.005 --> 45:08.671
Bye.

45:10.975 --> 45:11.741
Wow.

45:11.776 --> 45:12.909
Okay.

45:46.478 --> 45:50.813
[humming]
♪♪♪

45:50.849 --> 45:52.248
<i> Shouldn't you be on your way</i>
<i> to the wedding?</i>

45:52.283 --> 45:53.416
Dad!

45:53.451 --> 45:56.486
I'm just dropping off
some contracts for
Gloria to review

45:56.521 --> 45:57.453
while we're away.

45:57.489 --> 45:58.454
What are you doing here?

45:58.490 --> 45:59.856
Shouldn't you be
on the road?

45:59.891 --> 46:00.823
Well, we're going
to leave about 9:00.

46:00.859 --> 46:03.693
I... I just came in
to clean out my desk.

46:03.728 --> 46:06.829
Now the big office is going
to be yours soon.

46:06.865 --> 46:08.698
Just getting it ready
for you.

46:08.733 --> 46:10.466
You really can't wait
to get out of here

46:10.502 --> 46:11.934
and onto that golf course,
can you?

46:11.970 --> 46:13.569
[laughs]

46:16.174 --> 46:17.940
Well, I've spent some of
the best years of my life

46:17.976 --> 46:22.779
within these walls,
and now it's your turn.

46:22.814 --> 46:25.148
And you really loved it?

46:25.183 --> 46:27.150
Well, when you're given the
opportunity to build something

46:27.185 --> 46:30.553
that's yours and yours alone,
it's...

46:30.588 --> 46:33.856
there's no better feeling
in the world.

46:33.892 --> 46:39.195
You do what you love, and work
doesn't feel like work.

46:39.230 --> 46:43.065
You're gonna have a chance to
see that for yourself very soon.

46:43.101 --> 46:44.066
I know.

46:44.102 --> 46:45.034
Yeah.

46:45.069 --> 46:45.902
It's exciting.

46:45.937 --> 46:48.337
[laughs]
Yeah.

46:49.407 --> 46:50.873
I love you, Dad.

46:50.909 --> 46:52.775
I love you, Becca.

46:55.113 --> 46:56.312
Okay.

46:56.347 --> 46:59.382
Well, I will see you
at the resort.

46:59.417 --> 47:01.517
I'll see you there.
Drive safely.

47:01.553 --> 47:02.952
<i> You too!</i>

47:04.522 --> 47:09.325
♪

47:13.898 --> 47:15.498
Hey!

47:19.637 --> 47:20.837
So.

47:20.872 --> 47:21.604
Hey!

47:21.639 --> 47:23.606
Hi. Any advice for me?

47:23.641 --> 47:25.208
Advice?

47:25.243 --> 47:27.243
Well yeah, I'm officially
on the clock now, right?

47:27.278 --> 47:30.446
Oh, I've been on the clock
for three months, so...

47:30.481 --> 47:32.248
Well, in that case,
I'd better go find Craig

47:32.283 --> 47:34.383
and step up my game.

47:34.419 --> 47:37.520
But I will see you later
for a celebratory toast.

47:37.555 --> 47:38.721
<i> Great.</i>

47:38.756 --> 47:41.023
<i> I mean, we did make it this far</i>
<i> without getting fired.</i>

47:41.059 --> 47:45.027
Well, the weekend's still young,
so I'll see you inside.

47:45.063 --> 47:46.362
Sounds good.

47:49.934 --> 47:51.200
Hey.

47:51.236 --> 47:52.001
Hey!

47:52.036 --> 47:53.269
Can I give you a hand
with this?

47:53.304 --> 47:54.337
Where's all your stuff?

47:54.372 --> 47:56.639
My assistant's on his way up
with the equipment.

47:56.674 --> 47:58.140
You travel light.

47:58.176 --> 48:00.543
Oh, really?

48:01.913 --> 48:02.912
Mmhmm.

48:02.947 --> 48:04.080
[laughs]

48:04.515 --> 48:05.615
[laughing]

48:05.650 --> 48:09.452
Did you bring every item
you own?

48:09.487 --> 48:10.786
So, how are you feeling?

48:10.822 --> 48:11.654
Are you ready?

48:11.689 --> 48:12.688
No, I'm exhausted.

48:12.724 --> 48:14.724
I've had insurance all day,
and jewelry all night.

48:14.759 --> 48:16.259
I don't know which way
is up.

48:16.294 --> 48:17.260
But you got the collection in?

48:17.295 --> 48:18.494
Yesterday.

48:18.529 --> 48:20.496
But I've been burning the candle
at both ends for three weeks,

48:20.531 --> 48:23.733
so I've really got to pull it
together for Lucie.

48:24.502 --> 48:25.835
[elevator dings]

48:25.870 --> 48:27.670
So what about you, did you
meet your deadline?

48:27.705 --> 48:31.173
All downloaded
onto my tablet.

48:31.209 --> 48:32.275
You know, I...

48:32.310 --> 48:34.076
I often see my work differently
when someone else is

48:34.112 --> 48:35.378
in the room with me.

48:35.413 --> 48:38.414
If you're willing, I would love
to watch it through your eyes.

48:38.449 --> 48:39.515
You'll be my first
focus group.

48:39.550 --> 48:41.083
No one else has
seen it yet?

48:41.119 --> 48:43.986
Just the few clips I showed you
in the editing bay.

48:44.022 --> 48:45.655
I need someone I know
will take it seriously.

48:45.690 --> 48:47.023
I will.

48:47.058 --> 48:49.158
I know.

48:49.193 --> 48:52.595
Well, thank you
for your help.

48:52.630 --> 48:54.597
Anytime.

48:55.400 --> 48:57.667
So, tonight after
the cocktail party,

48:57.702 --> 49:00.836
that little library area
on the second floor?

49:00.872 --> 49:03.306
I'll be there.

49:08.880 --> 49:10.513
And I figured what better way
to welcome you

49:10.548 --> 49:12.982
than with a champagne toast?

49:13.017 --> 49:17.453
So I ask you to raise your glass
in cheers to my little girl

49:17.488 --> 49:19.055
and her husband to be.

49:19.090 --> 49:20.990
(All) Cheers!

49:21.025 --> 49:22.658
[glasses clink]

49:22.694 --> 49:24.493
I'm not going to cry.

49:24.529 --> 49:27.530
And now, let the wedding
weekend festivities begin!

49:27.565 --> 49:29.999
[cheering]

49:31.703 --> 49:32.802
<i> [lounge music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

49:32.837 --> 49:33.970
Oh, yeah.

49:34.005 --> 49:35.404
You're so handsome.

49:35.440 --> 49:36.372
<i> The bride and groom.</i>

49:36.407 --> 49:37.740
Oh, hey.

49:37.775 --> 49:39.475
Desperate situation right here.

49:39.510 --> 49:40.476
Yeah.

49:40.511 --> 49:41.711
There they are.

49:41.746 --> 49:42.712
Cheers to you two.

49:42.747 --> 49:44.847
Cheers, congrats.

49:44.882 --> 49:46.449
That's better.

49:49.087 --> 49:50.753
[chuckles]

49:50.788 --> 49:53.255
I'll see you
at our screening.

49:53.291 --> 49:58.694
<i> [lounge music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

49:58.730 --> 50:01.764
Is it bad that I've only been
here for three hours

50:01.799 --> 50:04.333
and my feet are already
killing me?

50:04.369 --> 50:06.402
[laughs]

50:06.437 --> 50:08.104
You know why.

50:08.139 --> 50:11.874
Because I choose fashion
over comfort?

50:11.909 --> 50:14.577
You're doing too much.

50:14.612 --> 50:16.846
I want you to take care
of yourself.

50:16.881 --> 50:17.713
I am.

50:17.749 --> 50:18.514
Ugh.

50:18.549 --> 50:20.282
Okay, I will.

50:20.318 --> 50:23.185
You really think you can
do both?

50:23.221 --> 50:24.086
Yes.

50:24.122 --> 50:25.254
I do.

50:25.289 --> 50:29.358
Your parents work 12-hour days,
and there's two of them.

50:29.394 --> 50:32.361
What's going to happen when
it's just you running the show?

50:32.397 --> 50:34.764
Maybe I'll hire more agents.

50:34.799 --> 50:38.234
I know you don't want
to disappoint them,

50:38.269 --> 50:41.604
but you need to pick a lane.

50:41.639 --> 50:44.407
Have you signed
those papers yet?

50:44.442 --> 50:46.208
I'm going to.

50:46.244 --> 50:49.412
And what if the jewelry
takes off?

50:49.447 --> 50:52.014
Then what happens?

50:56.487 --> 51:04.894
♪♪

51:06.330 --> 51:07.229
Oh.

51:07.265 --> 51:07.897
[laughs]

51:07.932 --> 51:08.898
I didn't know you were here.

51:08.933 --> 51:09.899
Just got here.

51:09.934 --> 51:14.437
I brought refreshments,
courtesy of Uncle Paul.

51:14.472 --> 51:15.638
Excellent.

51:15.673 --> 51:19.909
Thank you, Uncle Paul.

51:19.944 --> 51:21.243
You ready for this?

51:21.279 --> 51:22.945
So ready.

51:24.282 --> 51:25.881
[glasses clinking]

51:29.120 --> 51:31.921
<i> [inspirational music]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

51:31.956 --> 51:39.128
<i> (TV) The bond that our</i>
<i> service dogs have with</i>
<i> our military is deep.</i>

51:39.163 --> 51:42.531
<i> They protect each other,</i>
<i> and they need each other.</i>

51:42.567 --> 51:49.805
♪♪

51:49.841 --> 51:51.974
[dog barking]

51:57.482 --> 52:01.283
<i> Words can't express the emotios</i>
<i> I'm feeling right now.</i>

52:02.587 --> 52:07.756
[laugh cry]

52:10.361 --> 52:12.528
She reunited him with Emra.

52:12.563 --> 52:14.697
You didn't think I was going to
take you on a 90-minute journey

52:14.732 --> 52:16.332
for them not to be reunited.

52:16.367 --> 52:17.900
That'd be terrible filmmaking.

52:17.935 --> 52:20.169
I know, but that's what makes
this so special.

52:20.204 --> 52:22.204
I'm on the edge of my seat
waiting for this ending,

52:22.240 --> 52:24.039
and I know what's going
to happen.

52:24.075 --> 52:25.174
And your mother...

52:25.209 --> 52:26.308
Yep.

52:26.344 --> 52:27.476
What an incredible woman.

52:27.512 --> 52:29.411
When people see this...

52:29.447 --> 52:31.046
I mean, it's... it's obviously
not ready.

52:31.082 --> 52:33.315
The music is way too dark
at times,

52:33.351 --> 52:34.517
I gotta lighten that up...

52:34.552 --> 52:35.751
I... I did not notice
any of that,

52:35.786 --> 52:37.987
I was just so swept up
in the story.

52:38.022 --> 52:41.524
Yeah, but I... I see where
I have to tinker with it
a little bit.

52:41.559 --> 52:43.225
I know this is your passion
project,

52:43.261 --> 52:45.394
but this cannot exist
in a vacuum,

52:45.429 --> 52:47.429
you've got to put it
out there.

52:47.465 --> 52:48.697
You don't get a second chance.

52:48.733 --> 52:50.432
In this business, you gotta hook
them in the first few minutes,

52:50.468 --> 52:51.534
or they turn it off.

52:51.569 --> 52:53.502
This has to be perfect.

52:54.906 --> 52:59.275
♪♪

52:59.310 --> 53:01.510
Well, I wish you could see
in yourself

53:01.546 --> 53:04.780
what I just saw in you.

53:04.815 --> 53:05.581
Thank you.

53:05.616 --> 53:06.715
I mean, look.

53:06.751 --> 53:10.553
You know, I... I know it's good,
but it has to be great.

53:10.588 --> 53:13.522
You're not as discriminating
as these producers,

53:13.558 --> 53:16.759
and you actually like me, which
means you wanna like the film.

53:16.794 --> 53:18.694
So now, you're assuming
I like you?

53:18.729 --> 53:20.429
[laughs]

53:20.464 --> 53:21.864
Well, I don't mean
to be presumptuous.

53:21.899 --> 53:24.300
Well, I do, and I really
like your film,

53:24.335 --> 53:26.769
and I think you should take
the leap.

53:26.804 --> 53:28.537
So, what's keeping you
from taking the leap?

53:28.573 --> 53:30.472
I did.

53:30.508 --> 53:33.375
I'm just waiting to hear back
from the distributor.

53:33.411 --> 53:35.711
Come on, she's not the only
deal in town.

53:35.746 --> 53:38.380
My parents are so excited
to retire.

53:38.416 --> 53:40.649
And they still can, there's
other options for them, too.

53:40.685 --> 53:42.785
And don't you think they'd want
you to be doing what you love?

53:42.820 --> 53:44.386
I guess they think
I love insurance.

53:44.422 --> 53:45.154
But you don't.

53:45.189 --> 53:45.821
I don't.

53:45.856 --> 53:46.855
So, what are you going
to do?

53:46.891 --> 53:49.758
I don't know, but I have
some decisions to make.

53:49.794 --> 53:50.759
Hi.

53:50.795 --> 53:52.328
Do you have any pictures
of your jewelry on you?

53:52.363 --> 53:53.796
On my laptop.

53:53.831 --> 53:56.165
Email them to me.

53:56.200 --> 53:57.132
I want to show you
something.

53:57.168 --> 53:58.234
What?

53:58.269 --> 54:00.269
You'll see.

54:00.304 --> 54:01.837
Your story may still be
in progress,

54:01.872 --> 54:04.106
but maybe I can help find
the right ending.

54:06.777 --> 54:12.514
♪♪

54:12.550 --> 54:17.519
♪<i> Ooh, ooh</i> ♪

54:17.555 --> 54:22.191
♪<i> Ooh, ooh</i> ♪

54:22.226 --> 54:26.929
♪<i> Ooh, ooh</i> ♪

54:26.964 --> 54:28.097
♪<i> Ooh, ooh</i> ♪

54:28.132 --> 54:29.999
Penny for your thoughts?

54:30.034 --> 54:32.368
Just a moment of reflection.

54:32.403 --> 54:34.203
On what, if I may ask?

54:34.238 --> 54:35.771
Risk.

54:35.806 --> 54:37.640
Ah. Yes.

54:37.675 --> 54:38.674
A fine board game.

54:38.709 --> 54:40.509
[chuckles]

54:41.812 --> 54:43.012
I know you didn't ask
for any advice,

54:43.047 --> 54:46.348
but here's what I've
learned about risk.

54:46.384 --> 54:49.018
The grass may seem greener
from far away,

54:49.053 --> 54:53.022
but when you get up close and
everything comes into focus,

54:53.057 --> 54:55.958
it may turn out to just be
a bunch of brightly
coloured weeds.

54:55.993 --> 54:59.061
You speak from experience.

54:59.096 --> 55:00.162
Well, one day I woke up,
and I just,

55:00.197 --> 55:03.632
I wasn't sure if I wanted
to keep practicing law.

55:03.668 --> 55:06.502
So, I opened up a restaurant.

55:06.537 --> 55:07.670
Asian fusion.

55:07.705 --> 55:08.671
[laughs]

55:08.706 --> 55:10.039
It lasted 174 days.

55:10.074 --> 55:11.707
What happened?

55:11.742 --> 55:13.175
Well... It's fine.

55:13.210 --> 55:16.345
I learned, I grew,
I got smarter.

55:16.380 --> 55:17.746
And that's what our failures
are supposed to do,

55:17.782 --> 55:19.915
they're supposed to teach us.

55:19.950 --> 55:22.251
But enough about that, we should
be enjoying this beautiful day

55:22.286 --> 55:23.385
before we get called back.

55:23.421 --> 55:24.286
[laughs]

55:24.322 --> 55:26.722
You know this one has been
decidedly easy.

55:26.757 --> 55:28.057
Not a hiccup so far.

55:28.092 --> 55:29.892
That's not bad
for your first rodeo.

55:29.927 --> 55:30.693
Thank you.

55:30.728 --> 55:32.361
Thank you very much.

55:34.932 --> 55:35.864
There you are.

55:35.900 --> 55:37.199
I've been looking for you.

55:37.234 --> 55:39.001
We were on a walk,
what's wrong?

55:39.036 --> 55:39.768
Everything.

55:39.804 --> 55:40.536
Everything is wrong.

55:40.571 --> 55:41.870
Famous last words
back there?

55:41.906 --> 55:42.905
I jinxed it.

55:42.940 --> 55:45.374
Why don't you start by
telling us the first thing?

55:45.409 --> 55:47.176
Okay, how about this?

55:47.211 --> 55:49.611
Mabel, the wedding coordinator,
quit.

55:49.647 --> 55:51.914
What? She...
quit your wedding?

55:51.949 --> 55:52.948
She quit her job.

55:52.983 --> 55:53.649
She left.

55:53.684 --> 55:55.451
I have no wedding coordinator.

55:55.486 --> 55:56.418
There's no one.

55:56.454 --> 55:57.720
This is a disaster.

55:57.755 --> 55:58.754
A disaster.

55:58.789 --> 56:01.890
No, this is not a...
disaster.

56:01.926 --> 56:04.593
This is just a hiccup.

56:04.628 --> 56:06.528
An extremely dramatic case
of the hiccups.

56:06.564 --> 56:07.963
And peanut butter
will not help.

56:07.998 --> 56:12.534
Well we, uh, will just
do it together.

56:12.570 --> 56:13.902
Me and... and Aiden.

56:13.938 --> 56:15.637
We will?

56:15.673 --> 56:16.438
We will.

56:16.474 --> 56:18.040
Because that is what
we're here for.

56:18.075 --> 56:18.907
Can you do that?

56:18.943 --> 56:20.075
Yes.

56:20.111 --> 56:22.411
Because I am not going to let
anything ruin your wedding.

56:22.446 --> 56:24.613
Now you just go inside
and get dressed,

56:24.648 --> 56:25.914
and I will meet you there.

56:25.950 --> 56:26.915
With pantyhose.

56:26.951 --> 56:27.783
I forgot pantyhose.

56:27.818 --> 56:28.817
That was the other disaster.

56:28.853 --> 56:30.285
I brought you
four extra pairs.

56:30.321 --> 56:32.254
We got this.

56:32.289 --> 56:33.555
Where would I be
without you, Becks?

56:33.591 --> 56:35.257
In a car, on your way
to get pantyhose.

56:35.292 --> 56:36.959
Now go!

56:38.028 --> 56:38.961
[sighs]

56:38.996 --> 56:40.462
You're going to show me
what to do, right?

56:40.498 --> 56:44.233
Yes. As soon as I figure
it out myself.

56:55.446 --> 56:57.246
I still can't believe she quit.

56:57.281 --> 57:00.182
Luce, I have been to enough
of these to know how it works.

57:00.217 --> 57:02.184
It's fine.

57:02.219 --> 57:03.585
I hope so.

57:03.621 --> 57:04.653
Are you ready?

57:04.688 --> 57:06.355
No. I still need to work
on the processional order.

57:06.390 --> 57:08.657
Why don't you go ahead,
have a drink, I'll catch up.

57:08.692 --> 57:10.626
Just relax, try to stay present.

57:10.661 --> 57:11.760
I got this.

57:11.796 --> 57:12.795
[laughs]

57:12.830 --> 57:13.929
Thanks, Becks.

57:13.964 --> 57:16.165
Have fun!

57:16.200 --> 57:16.832
[door closes]

57:16.867 --> 57:18.500
I don't know if I got this.

57:19.670 --> 57:21.303
[whispers]
All right.

57:24.542 --> 57:25.340
[knocking at door]

57:25.376 --> 57:26.809
Luce?

57:27.578 --> 57:28.610
Luce?

57:28.646 --> 57:30.479
Did you forget your bag?

57:32.416 --> 57:33.549
Kyle.

57:33.584 --> 57:34.416
My assistant is setting up.

57:34.452 --> 57:35.851
I have to run down
to the greenhouse,

57:35.886 --> 57:37.853
but I wanted to show
you something.

57:37.888 --> 57:42.324
I worked on this last night
after our little screening.

57:47.598 --> 57:50.199
You did all of this
last night?

57:50.234 --> 57:53.936
It's just a mock-up,
for now.

57:59.109 --> 58:01.210
Anyway, you can hang
onto the tablet,

58:01.245 --> 58:04.246
take a look at it,
dare to dream,

58:04.281 --> 58:07.850
and please be careful,
my movie is on there.

58:08.919 --> 58:11.720
I will take great care
of this.

58:11.755 --> 58:14.022
Thank you, Kyle.

58:14.792 --> 58:15.724
What's wrong?

58:15.759 --> 58:16.725
Nothing.

58:16.760 --> 58:18.227
Nothing's wrong.

58:18.262 --> 58:19.495
No, everything is right.

58:19.530 --> 58:21.663
[tearfully] I don't
think anything

58:21.699 --> 58:24.733
has ever looked more right.

58:33.444 --> 58:37.980
down the aisle.

58:38.015 --> 58:39.748
<i> Lovely, lovely.</i>

58:39.783 --> 58:42.985
<i> You look beautiful.</i>

58:43.020 --> 58:44.686
Walk slowly,
give people time

58:44.722 --> 58:47.756
to enjoy those gorgeous
yellow dresses.

58:50.127 --> 58:52.194
I'm not being very helpful,
I'm sorry.

58:52.229 --> 58:53.929
But you really know how
to rise to a challenge,

58:53.964 --> 58:54.830
it's impressive.

58:54.865 --> 58:56.498
It's the job.

58:56.534 --> 58:57.933
<i> And next, before</i>
<i> the main event,</i>

58:57.968 --> 58:59.635
we have the maid of honour
and best man.

58:59.670 --> 59:00.669
Shall we?

59:00.704 --> 59:02.938
Yes, we shall.

59:02.973 --> 59:06.008
Aww, everyone looks
so perfect together.

59:06.043 --> 59:09.111
[laughs]

59:10.214 --> 59:12.481
[whispers] I will
say this, though.

59:12.516 --> 59:15.117
I don't know if they're
completely wrong.

59:15.152 --> 59:17.653
Their instincts, I mean.

59:18.355 --> 59:19.721
<i> Becca? Is it time?</i>

59:19.757 --> 59:20.522
<i> Yes.</i>

59:20.558 --> 59:21.323
When do I go?

59:21.358 --> 59:22.190
Yes. Cue the music
for the bride,

59:22.226 --> 59:24.359
so when I get to the end
of the aisle,

59:24.395 --> 59:25.627
you cue music,

59:25.663 --> 59:30.365
and we have the precious little
flower girl, go shine bright.

59:30.401 --> 59:32.568
Adorable.

59:32.603 --> 59:33.802
And now Uncle Paul.

59:33.837 --> 59:37.072
Wait a few seconds, and you may
take your walk down the aisle.

59:37.107 --> 59:46.915
[string music]
♪

59:46.951 --> 59:57.626
♪

1:00:11.909 --> 1:00:12.674
<i> Hey.</i>

1:00:12.710 --> 1:00:14.409
There you are.

1:00:14.445 --> 1:00:16.578
I was hoping I could grab you
for an interview

1:00:16.614 --> 1:00:18.213
since we have a few minutes
before the dinner party.

1:00:18.248 --> 1:00:19.848
You're going to interview me?

1:00:19.883 --> 1:00:21.450
Your uncle is requesting
testimonials

1:00:21.485 --> 1:00:24.586
from everyone in attendance.

1:00:24.622 --> 1:00:25.954
What do you say?

1:00:25.990 --> 1:00:29.124
Do you want to do a little
interrogation?

1:00:29.159 --> 1:00:32.027
Okay, let's do it.

1:00:33.998 --> 1:00:35.197
So, what are you going
to ask me?

1:00:35.232 --> 1:00:36.198
All the hard questions.

1:00:36.233 --> 1:00:37.065
Like what?

1:00:37.101 --> 1:00:38.066
Favourite colour.

1:00:38.102 --> 1:00:39.134
Favourite food.

1:00:39.169 --> 1:00:40.202
Favourite dinosaur.

1:00:40.237 --> 1:00:42.170
Dinosaur?

1:00:44.408 --> 1:00:48.243
So... What would you like
to say to Lucie?

1:00:48.278 --> 1:00:49.544
Hi Luce.

1:00:49.580 --> 1:00:51.613
Um, I love you.

1:00:51.649 --> 1:00:54.750
You are my cousin,
and my best friend,

1:00:54.785 --> 1:00:56.985
and I'm pretty sure you were
my mother in a past life,

1:00:57.021 --> 1:00:58.954
because you live to tell me
what to do.

1:00:58.989 --> 1:01:00.689
[laughs]

1:01:01.258 --> 1:01:03.158
[whispers] Can you
stop it for a second?

1:01:03.193 --> 1:01:04.726
Yeah.

1:01:07.931 --> 1:01:10.098
I really don't want this
to sound like all the other

1:01:10.134 --> 1:01:14.670
wedding interviews,
because for some reason,

1:01:14.705 --> 1:01:17.172
this doesn't feel like
all the other weddings.

1:01:17.207 --> 1:01:19.274
Maybe things are changing.

1:01:19.309 --> 1:01:22.411
Maybe.

1:01:22.446 --> 1:01:25.814
Tell me what you think
is special about Lucie.

1:01:25.849 --> 1:01:29.351
Well, you know how
there are people who,

1:01:29.386 --> 1:01:31.186
they just do things
their own way.

1:01:31.221 --> 1:01:36.191
And they don't follow the rules,
and always come out ahead.

1:01:36.226 --> 1:01:40.829
I used to say that Lucie was
born under a lucky star.

1:01:40.864 --> 1:01:42.531
And then she would
always say to me,

1:01:42.566 --> 1:01:45.434
"it's not luck, you just have
to believe you can have

1:01:45.469 --> 1:01:47.436
what you want.

1:01:47.471 --> 1:01:49.304
She's right.

1:01:49.339 --> 1:01:51.106
I know.

1:01:54.144 --> 1:01:57.646
Let's try that one more time,
for the camera.

1:02:00.551 --> 1:02:03.285
Three, two, one...

1:02:03.320 --> 1:02:04.853
[laughs]

1:02:06.023 --> 1:02:14.463
<i> [dance music]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

1:02:14.498 --> 1:02:15.831
They look happy,
don't they?

1:02:15.866 --> 1:02:17.499
How could they not be?

1:02:17.534 --> 1:02:19.034
<i> They're getting married</i>
<i> tomorrow.</i>

1:02:19.069 --> 1:02:20.502
It's perfect.

1:02:20.537 --> 1:02:22.370
You sure do know how
to throw a party.

1:02:22.406 --> 1:02:26.041
Well, you have been such
a help.

1:02:26.076 --> 1:02:27.709
You keep the calm.

1:02:27.745 --> 1:02:28.643
Lucie tends to spin.

1:02:28.679 --> 1:02:30.746
I haven't seen even
a moment of stress.

1:02:30.781 --> 1:02:33.248
Maybe I'm just hiding it
from you.

1:02:33.283 --> 1:02:34.649
[laughs]

1:02:34.685 --> 1:02:36.184
We're family, it's what we do.

1:02:36.220 --> 1:02:36.985
And trust me,

1:02:37.020 --> 1:02:39.020
I'm gonna call in a lot
of favours

1:02:39.056 --> 1:02:40.655
when and if my time comes.

1:02:40.691 --> 1:02:41.990
Oh, it'll come.

1:02:42.025 --> 1:02:44.359
I'm not worried about you
at all, Becks.

1:02:44.394 --> 1:02:47.095
[slow rock music]
♪♪

1:02:47.131 --> 1:02:49.197
Becca.

1:02:49.233 --> 1:02:51.066
May I have this dance?

1:02:51.101 --> 1:02:52.768
Sure.

1:02:52.803 --> 1:03:03.011
♪

1:03:03.046 --> 1:03:13.054
♪

1:03:16.794 --> 1:03:17.959
<i> [energetic pop music]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

1:03:17.995 --> 1:03:19.861
♪<i> This girl's on my mind</i> ♪

1:03:19.897 --> 1:03:21.029
♪<i> This girl's on my mind</i> ♪

1:03:21.064 --> 1:03:23.398
♪<i> Hey, yeah</i> ♪

1:03:23.433 --> 1:03:28.436
♪

1:03:28.472 --> 1:03:34.543
♪<i> Now, everything feels</i>
<i> so good, so right</i> ♪

1:03:34.578 --> 1:03:36.611
Did you get a chance to review
the rest of the website yet?

1:03:36.647 --> 1:03:38.146
I will, as soon as
I'm off the clock.

1:03:38.182 --> 1:03:39.281
All right.

1:03:39.316 --> 1:03:41.383
Don't forget to fill in
the section about your story.

1:03:41.418 --> 1:03:43.218
And remember,

1:03:43.253 --> 1:03:46.254
it's still up to you to decide
how it ends.

1:03:59.603 --> 1:04:00.836
<i> Making the jump from insurance</i>

1:04:00.871 --> 1:04:06.374
<i> to starting my own jewelry</i>
<i> business was not an easy one.</i>

1:04:11.348 --> 1:04:14.182
<i> But sometimes, when passion</i>
<i> is involved,</i>

1:04:14.218 --> 1:04:16.585
<i> it's evident that you must take</i>
<i> the leap</i>

1:04:16.620 --> 1:04:20.622
<i> and trust that the net</i>
<i> will appear beneath you.</i>

1:04:20.657 --> 1:04:22.524
<i> And so with every piece</i>
<i> I design,</i>

1:04:22.559 --> 1:04:25.927
<i> I inspire my customers</i>
<i> to follow your dreams</i>

1:04:25.963 --> 1:04:29.464
<i> and shine like the jewels</i>
<i> that we all are.</i>

1:04:38.475 --> 1:04:39.441
Hey.

1:04:39.476 --> 1:04:41.142
You done for the night?

1:04:41.178 --> 1:04:43.612
Yeah, it's just your Uncle Paul
and his buddies in the bar.

1:04:43.647 --> 1:04:46.615
They told me to gather
my strength for tomorrow.

1:04:46.650 --> 1:04:48.650
Well, maybe doesn't want
evidence of their shenanigans.

1:04:48.685 --> 1:04:49.484
[laughs]

1:04:49.519 --> 1:04:50.185
Not to worry, though.

1:04:50.220 --> 1:04:52.287
Edit out the messy stuff, right?

1:04:52.322 --> 1:04:54.456
Always.

1:04:54.491 --> 1:04:58.727
What are you doing
out here all alone?

1:04:58.762 --> 1:04:59.928
It's rough.

1:04:59.963 --> 1:05:06.868
I, uh, need to work on it
further before it goes online.

1:05:06.904 --> 1:05:10.038
But I'm in.

1:05:10.073 --> 1:05:11.373
You sure about this?

1:05:11.408 --> 1:05:12.807
You haven't even heard
from the distributor.

1:05:12.843 --> 1:05:14.476
I don't need to.

1:05:14.511 --> 1:05:17.145
I'm not signing the papers.

1:05:17.180 --> 1:05:19.948
I'm going into the jewelry
business.

1:05:21.518 --> 1:05:24.953
[laughs]

1:05:30.627 --> 1:05:32.027
ow.

1:05:32.062 --> 1:05:33.395
What is?

1:05:33.430 --> 1:05:36.231
Watching you take such
a brave step.

1:05:36.266 --> 1:05:38.600
Well, making the decision
was the easy part.

1:05:38.635 --> 1:05:40.268
I still have to tell
my parents.

1:05:40.304 --> 1:05:42.537
This decision doesn't
just affect me.

1:05:42.572 --> 1:05:43.705
I know.

1:05:43.740 --> 1:05:45.407
But they're good people.

1:05:45.442 --> 1:05:49.945
I'm sure if they knew how
you really felt...

1:05:49.980 --> 1:05:51.813
[laughs]

1:05:51.848 --> 1:06:02.490
♪♪

1:06:02.526 --> 1:06:05.894
I'm not great at letting
people in.

1:06:05.929 --> 1:06:10.565
You know, battle scars
and all.

1:06:10.600 --> 1:06:13.234
Safe and guarded.

1:06:15.806 --> 1:06:16.738
I don't know.

1:06:16.773 --> 1:06:19.007
Maybe we can't always
protect yourselves.

1:06:19.042 --> 1:06:20.842
No, we can't.

1:06:20.877 --> 1:06:22.944
You need to put your movie
out there, Kyle.

1:06:22.980 --> 1:06:24.145
I know.

1:06:24.181 --> 1:06:27.649
And I will.

1:06:27.684 --> 1:06:30.952
That's not really what
I'm talking about here.

1:06:33.290 --> 1:06:39.127
Without even realizing it, I
let my guard down with you.

1:06:39.162 --> 1:06:40.428
Maybe that's what you meant
when you said

1:06:40.464 --> 1:06:43.498
it should all be effortless.

1:06:43.533 --> 1:06:46.634
Yeah, I think I did that too.

1:06:49.740 --> 1:06:51.539
<i> (Lucie) Becca!</i>

1:06:51.575 --> 1:06:53.008
<i> Becks, are you out here?</i>

1:06:53.043 --> 1:06:56.444
Oh. I should probably...

1:06:56.480 --> 1:06:59.247
[laughing]

1:07:02.519 --> 1:07:03.852
Hang onto that.

1:07:03.887 --> 1:07:05.286
Finish it.

1:07:05.322 --> 1:07:07.022
We'll get it online.

1:07:08.158 --> 1:07:10.592
Goodnight.

1:07:18.335 --> 1:07:19.401
There you are.

1:07:19.436 --> 1:07:22.137
I was just taking a walk,
looking up at the stars.

1:07:22.172 --> 1:07:23.705
It's so beautiful here.

1:07:23.740 --> 1:07:24.973
I know, right?

1:07:25.008 --> 1:07:27.175
It's the perfect place
to get married.

1:07:27.210 --> 1:07:29.844
I'm ready to turn in, and I
wanted to see if you were too.

1:07:29.880 --> 1:07:31.046
We could do those face masks.

1:07:31.081 --> 1:07:31.880
Of course.

1:07:31.915 --> 1:07:33.848
I will not be puffy
on my wedding day.

1:07:33.884 --> 1:07:35.417
I would never let
that happen.

1:07:35.452 --> 1:07:37.385
You know how serious
I take this.

1:07:37.421 --> 1:07:39.187
I know.

1:07:40.290 --> 1:07:47.362
<i> [elegant string music]</i>
<i> ♪♪</i>

1:07:47.397 --> 1:07:58.406
♪

1:08:11.154 --> 1:08:13.254
[phone ringing]

1:08:13.290 --> 1:08:14.155
Hello?

1:08:14.191 --> 1:08:16.391
<i> It's Holly from</i>
<i> the bridal boutique.</i>

1:08:16.426 --> 1:08:18.359
Oh, hi Holly.

1:08:18.395 --> 1:08:19.394
So listen.

1:08:19.429 --> 1:08:22.230
I know it's Lucie's wedding day
and you're busy,

1:08:22.265 --> 1:08:24.632
but I couldn't wait
to share the news.

1:08:24.668 --> 1:08:26.701
<i> Gretchen, our</i>
<i> jewelry distributor,</i>

1:08:26.736 --> 1:08:28.636
<i> loved the pieces.</i>

1:08:28.672 --> 1:08:30.138
<i> She wants to meet with you</i>
<i> next week.</i>

1:08:30.173 --> 1:08:32.740
Oh Holly, this is
great news.

1:08:32.776 --> 1:08:34.609
So go, enjoy yourself,

1:08:34.644 --> 1:08:37.579
and I'm sending her all of
your information.

1:08:37.614 --> 1:08:39.647
<i> She'll be in touch.</i>

1:08:39.683 --> 1:08:41.649
Thank you for doing this.

1:08:41.685 --> 1:08:43.585
<i> It was my pleasure, truly.</i>

1:08:43.620 --> 1:08:46.154
I will talk to you soon.
Bye!

1:08:46.189 --> 1:08:47.622
<i> Bye.</i>

1:08:50.260 --> 1:08:51.126
Hey, Becks.

1:08:51.161 --> 1:08:51.993
Uncle Paul.

1:08:52.028 --> 1:08:53.294
Just taking a few minutes
to yourself?

1:08:53.330 --> 1:08:55.063
Lucie's getting an
in-room massage,

1:08:55.098 --> 1:08:57.465
so I'm just hanging out here
until we start getting ready.

1:08:57.501 --> 1:08:59.634
Oh.

1:08:59.669 --> 1:09:00.969
What are you watching?

1:09:01.004 --> 1:09:02.403
Uh, nothing.

1:09:02.439 --> 1:09:05.773
Just a... a friend's
thing.

1:09:05.809 --> 1:09:07.275
Military dogs?

1:09:07.310 --> 1:09:09.978
It's a documentary.

1:09:10.013 --> 1:09:12.013
And a friend of yours
made this?

1:09:12.048 --> 1:09:15.116
Kyle, actually,
the videographer.

1:09:15.152 --> 1:09:18.153
Oh. Good guy.

1:09:18.188 --> 1:09:19.621
He is.

1:09:19.656 --> 1:09:20.688
Let me take a look.

1:09:20.724 --> 1:09:22.524
Um, I'm just killing time
before the big event,

1:09:22.559 --> 1:09:27.462
I could really use
a distraction.

1:09:27.497 --> 1:09:28.596
Okay.

1:09:28.632 --> 1:09:29.597
Oh, great.

1:09:29.633 --> 1:09:31.099
Um.

1:09:42.045 --> 1:09:44.746
Oh, wow.

1:10:01.064 --> 1:10:03.131
Oh, Luce!

1:10:03.166 --> 1:10:04.799
It's perfect.

1:10:04.834 --> 1:10:05.800
Don't start.

1:10:05.835 --> 1:10:07.902
We can't have our makeup
running before pictures.

1:10:07.938 --> 1:10:11.673
Oh, I know, I know,
but wow!

1:10:11.708 --> 1:10:14.075
I know.

1:10:14.110 --> 1:10:18.980
Thank you for making this day
so special

1:10:19.015 --> 1:10:23.885
and for protecting me,
and alleviating any stress.

1:10:23.920 --> 1:10:25.486
And making sure
I'm not puffy.

1:10:25.522 --> 1:10:26.487
[chuckles]

1:10:26.523 --> 1:10:28.223
It's what I do.

1:10:28.258 --> 1:10:29.691
[knocking at door]

1:10:29.726 --> 1:10:31.859
Oh, I'll get it,
I'll get it.

1:10:38.101 --> 1:10:41.202
Wow. You look...

1:10:41.238 --> 1:10:43.571
Even in the yellow.

1:10:43.607 --> 1:10:46.874
Aren't you supposed to
be looking at the bride?

1:10:49.646 --> 1:10:51.546
I can't.

1:10:53.149 --> 1:10:54.349
How about you help her
with her veil,

1:10:54.384 --> 1:10:55.750
and I'll get some footage.

1:10:55.785 --> 1:10:57.352
Okay.

1:10:59.322 --> 1:11:01.022
Kyle, I am a little shaky,

1:11:01.057 --> 1:11:03.391
so try not to let it show
on camera.

1:11:03.426 --> 1:11:05.627
<i> You look stunning, Lucie.</i>

1:11:05.662 --> 1:11:08.029
The most beautiful bride
I've ever seen.

1:11:08.064 --> 1:11:10.064
I bet you say that
to all your brides.

1:11:10.100 --> 1:11:11.299
I do.

1:11:11.334 --> 1:11:13.434
But this time I mean it.

1:11:19.075 --> 1:11:21.876
Okay. Straighten that,
that looks fabulous.

1:11:21.911 --> 1:11:23.611
Top button.

1:11:23.647 --> 1:11:24.879
All right. You're good to go.

1:11:24.914 --> 1:11:25.913
Thank you.

1:11:30.020 --> 1:11:30.785
Hi, Kyle.

1:11:30.820 --> 1:11:32.153
You getting everything
you need?

1:11:32.188 --> 1:11:33.121
Yeah, great.

1:11:33.156 --> 1:11:34.789
I've got all the angles covered
you asked for.

1:11:34.824 --> 1:11:35.890
Ah, that's great.

1:11:35.925 --> 1:11:37.492
We're just a few minutes away
from the big reveal.

1:11:37.527 --> 1:11:38.626
It's always a production.

1:11:38.662 --> 1:11:39.427
[laughs]

1:11:39.462 --> 1:11:40.828
That it is.

1:11:40.864 --> 1:11:42.163
Now, I wonder why
you never mentioned

1:11:42.198 --> 1:11:44.499
that you're a filmmaker.

1:11:44.534 --> 1:11:46.668
I just do everything I can
to properly capture

1:11:46.703 --> 1:11:47.769
the special day.

1:11:47.804 --> 1:11:49.504
No, no, I'm not talking about
your wedding videos.

1:11:49.539 --> 1:11:50.672
I mean your film.

1:11:50.707 --> 1:11:53.274
The military dogs.

1:11:53.310 --> 1:11:55.009
I'm sorry, I...
I'm not sure...

1:11:55.045 --> 1:11:57.245
Now, I haven't had a chance
to watch all of it yet, but...

1:11:57.280 --> 1:11:57.979
How did you?...

1:11:58.014 --> 1:11:59.447
Oh, well, Becca
showed it to me.

1:11:59.482 --> 1:12:00.548
Obviously it's kind of
a busy day,

1:12:00.583 --> 1:12:02.483
I won't be able to watch
the rest of it till tomorrow.

1:12:02.519 --> 1:12:05.486
No, it's not ready.

1:12:05.522 --> 1:12:07.822
Oh, no, I've seen my share
of rough cuts.

1:12:07.857 --> 1:12:08.756
But full disclosure,

1:12:08.792 --> 1:12:12.260
I don't normally deal
in documentaries.

1:12:12.295 --> 1:12:15.129
Oh, it's showtime.

1:12:15.165 --> 1:12:17.332
We'll finish this later.

1:12:19.402 --> 1:12:20.268
<i> Okay, bridesmaids.</i>

1:12:20.303 --> 1:12:21.202
<i> Everyone has their</i>
<i> dress straps up?</i>

1:12:21.237 --> 1:12:23.604
<i> Great, sorry,</i>
<i> Lucie changed her mind.</i>

1:12:23.640 --> 1:12:24.872
I'm going to cue
the processional music

1:12:24.908 --> 1:12:26.774
two minutes, smiles on.

1:12:26.810 --> 1:12:28.142
Hey, I got Lucie calmed down.

1:12:28.178 --> 1:12:30.345
No more shaking,
only pure excitement.

1:12:30.380 --> 1:12:31.279
That's great.

1:12:31.314 --> 1:12:33.114
As it should be.

1:12:34.551 --> 1:12:36.351
All right, if I could just get
everybody to find your partner,

1:12:36.386 --> 1:12:38.853
I want to do a walking shot
down the whole line of you.

1:12:38.888 --> 1:12:40.221
And also, I talked
to the banquet manager,

1:12:40.256 --> 1:12:41.522
and she's going to keep us
on schedule

1:12:41.558 --> 1:12:43.057
so I can enjoy
the reception.

1:12:43.093 --> 1:12:44.959
Great.

1:12:44.994 --> 1:12:46.961
Kyle.

1:12:46.996 --> 1:12:48.563
What's wrong?

1:12:48.598 --> 1:12:50.331
Look, I have a job to do,

1:12:50.367 --> 1:12:51.466
and you have an even
bigger one

1:12:51.501 --> 1:12:53.835
Somehow, you managed to squeeze
in a little screening

1:12:53.870 --> 1:12:56.304
with your uncle.

1:12:56.339 --> 1:12:59.240
I told you it
wasn't ready.

1:12:59.275 --> 1:13:01.676
Kyle, he saw me watching it.

1:13:01.711 --> 1:13:03.811
He knows it's not
the final version,

1:13:03.847 --> 1:13:04.912
it's... it's okay.

1:13:04.948 --> 1:13:08.850
No, no, it's not okay.

1:13:08.885 --> 1:13:11.719
I decide who sees it,
and I decide when.

1:13:11.755 --> 1:13:12.987
You gave away my
first impression

1:13:13.022 --> 1:13:18.159
before the film was even ready,
and I will never get that back.

1:13:18.194 --> 1:13:19.494
I'm going back to work.

1:13:19.529 --> 1:13:21.629
We're holding up the wedding.

1:13:22.198 --> 1:13:25.900
All right, everybody.
Looking great.

1:13:33.576 --> 1:13:43.384
♪♪

1:13:43.420 --> 1:13:53.227
♪

1:13:53.263 --> 1:13:54.896
♪

1:13:54.931 --> 1:13:58.166
♪<i> Feel it too</i> ♪

1:13:58.201 --> 1:14:02.136
♪

1:14:02.172 --> 1:14:04.906
♪<i> Moving closer</i> ♪

1:14:04.941 --> 1:14:06.240
♪<i> Remember that first kiss</i> ♪

1:14:06.276 --> 1:14:08.743
-I do.
-I do.

1:14:08.778 --> 1:14:12.680
♪

1:14:12.715 --> 1:14:22.623
♪<i> I've been waiting</i>
<i> for a love like this</i> ♪

1:14:22.659 --> 1:14:25.526
♪<i> Feel my heart,</i>
<i> it beats</i> ♪

1:14:25.562 --> 1:14:34.368
[cheering]

1:14:34.404 --> 1:14:39.307
♪<i> Tell me if you</i>
<i> feel it too</i> ♪

1:14:39.342 --> 1:14:44.278
♪

1:14:44.314 --> 1:14:50.818
<i> ♪ Tell me if you</i>
<i> feel it too ♪</i>

1:14:51.187 --> 1:14:53.788
[engine rattles loudly]

1:15:01.998 --> 1:15:03.464
Becca?

1:15:03.500 --> 1:15:05.399
There's someone I want you
to meet.

1:15:05.435 --> 1:15:07.034
She's a co-worker
of your uncle's,

1:15:07.070 --> 1:15:08.569
and her husband's
a realtor.

1:15:08.605 --> 1:15:11.038
He wants to connect you
with all his clients

1:15:11.074 --> 1:15:12.640
for their insurance needs.

1:15:12.675 --> 1:15:13.975
Mom.

1:15:14.010 --> 1:15:15.977
It's a huge opportunity
for you as you take over
the business.

1:15:16.012 --> 1:15:16.744
Mom... Let me-

1:15:16.779 --> 1:15:18.713
Wait.

1:15:18.748 --> 1:15:20.915
What's going on with you,
Becca.

1:15:20.950 --> 1:15:24.151
Look, I am so proud
of our company.

1:15:24.187 --> 1:15:27.221
Of what you and dad built,
but...

1:15:27.257 --> 1:15:29.090
You're not taking over.

1:15:29.125 --> 1:15:31.158
I want to give my jewelry
a shot.

1:15:31.194 --> 1:15:32.827
Full time.

1:15:32.862 --> 1:15:36.197
I've been juggling both,
and it's just not possible.

1:15:36.232 --> 1:15:37.498
Why didn't you tell us, honey?

1:15:37.534 --> 1:15:39.267
Because it meant
so much to you.

1:15:39.302 --> 1:15:41.836
Only because we thought
it's what you wanted.

1:15:41.871 --> 1:15:44.438
But I'm ruining your plans.

1:15:44.474 --> 1:15:46.173
Do you know how many offers
we've had on our business

1:15:46.209 --> 1:15:47.375
over the years?

1:15:47.410 --> 1:15:49.076
It's very successful,
you know.

1:15:49.112 --> 1:15:51.012
I do know.

1:15:51.047 --> 1:15:53.047
Although, I am going to let
you tell your father

1:15:53.082 --> 1:15:56.050
that he has to wait a little bit
longer for his retirement.

1:15:56.085 --> 1:15:56.918
[laughs]

1:15:56.953 --> 1:15:57.785
I'll tell him tomorrow.

1:15:57.820 --> 1:16:00.021
Let's let him enjoy
the wedding tonight.

1:16:00.056 --> 1:16:01.656
Thank you, Mom.

1:16:06.262 --> 1:16:10.631
Hey. There you are.

1:16:10.667 --> 1:16:11.699
Becca, I can't talk
right now.

1:16:11.734 --> 1:16:14.302
Just hear me out, please.

1:16:14.337 --> 1:16:16.070
Look, I'm sorry
if I overstepped,

1:16:16.105 --> 1:16:18.606
but your movie is ready.

1:16:18.641 --> 1:16:20.908
With all due respect, that
wasn't your decision to make.

1:16:20.944 --> 1:16:23.444
A few tweaks isn't going to
change the heart of the story,

1:16:23.479 --> 1:16:25.546
which is beautiful.

1:16:25.582 --> 1:16:27.915
And even though my uncle
only saw the first few minutes,

1:16:27.951 --> 1:16:29.150
he was intrigued.

1:16:29.185 --> 1:16:31.052
Of course he's going to say
that, standing in front of you.

1:16:31.087 --> 1:16:32.720
You're family. You asked him
for a favour.

1:16:32.755 --> 1:16:34.488
He asked me what I was watching.

1:16:34.524 --> 1:16:36.824
I reluctantly shared it
with him.

1:16:36.859 --> 1:16:38.259
But he doesn't mince words.

1:16:38.294 --> 1:16:40.294
He was impressed.
He is impressed.

1:16:43.466 --> 1:16:45.333
Look, something powerful
has happened

1:16:45.368 --> 1:16:49.971
over the past five months,
and I think it has for you too.

1:16:50.006 --> 1:16:52.006
You can deny yourself
of what's meant to be,

1:16:52.041 --> 1:16:55.843
but I'm not going
to do that anymore.

1:16:55.878 --> 1:17:00.414
And I will never apologize
for what I see in you.

1:17:14.864 --> 1:17:17.298
Always thinking, ruminating,
aren't you?

1:17:17.333 --> 1:17:18.432
Well, you gotta admit,

1:17:18.468 --> 1:17:21.836
this is a pretty great place
to process your thoughts.

1:17:21.871 --> 1:17:22.803
[sighs]

1:17:22.839 --> 1:17:24.038
Yeah.

1:17:24.073 --> 1:17:28.876
I've come to a few new
revelations here myself,
actually.

1:17:31.247 --> 1:17:36.684
Aiden, I think you are
a great guy.

1:17:36.719 --> 1:17:38.419
But?

1:17:38.454 --> 1:17:42.023
But my heart belong
somewhere else,

1:17:42.058 --> 1:17:45.593
and even though I don't think
that's going anywhere,

1:17:45.628 --> 1:17:47.662
it wouldn't be fair
to either of us

1:17:47.697 --> 1:17:52.333
if I pursued something
with you.

1:17:52.368 --> 1:17:55.036
I appreciate your honesty.

1:17:55.071 --> 1:18:01.842
Uh, and whoever this guy is,
he is crazy for not seeing

1:18:01.878 --> 1:18:04.545
what's right in front of him.

1:18:07.050 --> 1:18:08.582
<i> There you are.</i>

1:18:08.618 --> 1:18:09.316
Aiden.

1:18:09.352 --> 1:18:11.886
The guys need you
for a photo.

1:18:11.921 --> 1:18:13.688
Okay.

1:18:15.091 --> 1:18:17.358
[sighs]

1:18:27.603 --> 1:18:32.039
[ambient chattering]

1:18:45.955 --> 1:18:47.421
Hello!

1:18:48.524 --> 1:18:50.291
Hello!

1:18:51.661 --> 1:18:52.760
[laughs]

1:18:52.795 --> 1:18:54.628
I had a speech prepared
tonight,

1:18:54.664 --> 1:18:56.063
as you know I always do.

1:18:56.099 --> 1:18:58.132
[laughs]

1:18:58.167 --> 1:19:02.436
But I think I want this one to
come straight from the heart.

1:19:03.673 --> 1:19:06.340
I've always said that love
should be instant

1:19:06.375 --> 1:19:08.342
and effortless.

1:19:08.377 --> 1:19:10.945
When you find that person,
there's no struggle,

1:19:10.980 --> 1:19:12.646
there' s no drama,

1:19:12.682 --> 1:19:16.951
you get to be you
and your loved for it.

1:19:16.986 --> 1:19:21.589
But I think I was wrong
about the instant part.

1:19:21.624 --> 1:19:24.125
Watching Lucie and Craig
grow together

1:19:24.160 --> 1:19:25.059
over the past few years,

1:19:25.094 --> 1:19:29.163
I see that true love
is about continually

1:19:29.198 --> 1:19:31.332
lifting each other up.

